WEBVTT

01:53.193 --> 01:54.786
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

02:09.876 --> 02:11.867
[SIRENS WAILING]

02:14.681 --> 02:16.615
[APPLAUSE]

02:16.783 --> 02:18.774
[CROWD CHEERING]

02:47.214 --> 02:51.412
Red backpack, your right, my left.

02:51.585 --> 02:53.110
WOMAN 1:
Jimmy, four more years!

02:57.524 --> 02:58.821
Four more years!

02:58.992 --> 03:01.654
- Four more years, Jimmy!
- See him?

03:06.933 --> 03:07.991
WOMAN 2:
Hey, watch it.

03:08.168 --> 03:09.363
MAN 1:
Hey, come on.

03:09.536 --> 03:11.231
WOMAN 3:
Excuse you.

03:20.547 --> 03:22.538
- Excuse me.
MAN 2: Hey, easy.

03:22.749 --> 03:23.944
- I'm so sorry.
MAN 3: Hey!

03:24.117 --> 03:27.314
Whoa, there. You have to wait in line
just like everyone else.

03:27.487 --> 03:30.320
I think I'm gonna miss my flight.
You think we could just--?

03:30.490 --> 03:33.050
If I could skip ahead?
I don't wanna miss my flight.

03:33.260 --> 03:35.058
OFFICER:
Open the bag for me, sir.

03:35.262 --> 03:37.959
- I don't wanna miss my flight.
- Open the bag for me, sir.

03:38.131 --> 03:41.226
- Yeah, I just-- I'm just in a hurry.
- What time is your flight?

03:41.401 --> 03:44.302
- It's soon. I think they're boarding now.
- Open the bag, sir.

03:44.471 --> 03:46.872
[WOMAN SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY
OVER PA]

03:54.281 --> 03:55.806
Wayne.

04:01.288 --> 04:03.052
WAYNE:
Jesus H. Christ, son.

04:03.223 --> 04:04.384
Come here.

04:04.558 --> 04:07.858
Hoping for a slow day.
You have the right to remain silent.

04:08.028 --> 04:10.793
Anything you say can and will be used
against you in a court of law.

04:14.301 --> 04:17.168
WOMAN <i>[ON</i> TV]: <i>Reagan said he didn't come
to the South Bronx to make promises...</i>

04:17.337 --> 04:18.531
<i>...but because Jimmy Carter...</i>

04:18.704 --> 04:21.902
<i>...hadn't kept his promise
to help the blighted area recover.</i>

04:22.075 --> 04:25.272
<i>But as Reagan talked to reporters
about getting the economy moving...</i>

04:25.445 --> 04:27.880
<i>...a crowd of young people
chanted and booed him.</i>

04:28.048 --> 04:30.517
CROWD [CHANTING]:
Speak to the people, not the press!

04:30.684 --> 04:33.710
WOMAN: <i>Reagan finally waded
into the crowd to try to talk.</i>

04:33.887 --> 04:38.347
<i>- What are you gonna do to help?
- Jobs, development zones. You will get jobs.</i>

04:38.525 --> 04:40.789
<i>You're a racist trying
to get in the White House.</i>

04:40.961 --> 04:43.123
<i>- What are you gonna do to help us?
REAGAN: I'm trying to tell you!</i>

04:43.330 --> 04:46.356
<i>I can't do a damn thing for you
unless I get elected!</i>

04:46.533 --> 04:48.365
<i>- Ronnie, come on.
- AH right, get out!</i>

04:48.535 --> 04:50.128
CROWD [CHANTING]:
Go back home!

04:50.337 --> 04:52.328
- Go back home!
- Turn it off.

04:53.840 --> 04:56.810
[SIGHING]
Well, that was a disaster.

04:56.977 --> 04:59.105
It's leading every news broadcast,
even CNN.

04:59.279 --> 05:03.375
Governor, it would be nice
if you would just stick to the script.

05:04.584 --> 05:07.918
I was not gonna let that man call me a racist.

05:08.088 --> 05:11.080
Carter's fault, governor.
He's been real bold with the racist rhetoric.

05:11.257 --> 05:14.887
He wants us to panic, and then we do.
We're not disciplined enough.

05:15.061 --> 05:17.621
TIME magazine's latest polls
have us down by three points.

05:18.131 --> 05:21.465
And The New York Times,
they're gonna endorse Jimmy Carter.

05:21.635 --> 05:25.333
Then there's these rumblings
the Carter folks are working with the Iranians...

05:25.505 --> 05:28.065
...to release the hostages
right before the election.

05:28.241 --> 05:31.142
- The October surprise.
- The public will see right through that.

05:31.311 --> 05:34.941
What the public will see
are 52 freed Americans.

05:35.115 --> 05:39.609
Well, anybody else got something to say?

05:40.253 --> 05:41.379
I think Jim does.

05:43.657 --> 05:47.616
Mr. Casey, if I may.
I know I'm the new kid on the block.

05:47.794 --> 05:51.094
I mean, I wasn't around when you all had
your 20-point lead and all.

05:51.765 --> 05:55.258
But it seems to me we're just a little bit tight.

05:55.669 --> 05:58.661
Governor, why do you wanna be president?

05:58.838 --> 06:00.829
[ALL CHUCKLING]

06:01.007 --> 06:02.202
You don't know?

06:02.409 --> 06:03.706
Well, let's pretend I don't.

06:03.910 --> 06:07.175
Just as simple as you can,
distill it down to its essence, so to speak.

06:08.948 --> 06:11.212
Well, we're at sea.

06:11.418 --> 06:14.479
The country's lost and I know the way back.

06:14.654 --> 06:16.986
How? How do we get back?

06:18.024 --> 06:24.953
Get the government off the people's backs,
fix the economy, and beat the Russians.

06:25.131 --> 06:27.031
That sounds like a good direction to me.

06:27.200 --> 06:28.998
You know, I heard you give...

06:29.169 --> 06:33.800
...one of the most awe-inspiring speeches
I have ever heard at the '76 convention.

06:34.441 --> 06:37.069
You'd just lost to Gerald Ford,
my candidate.

06:37.243 --> 06:40.440
Yeah, because you stole our delegates.

06:41.448 --> 06:45.248
But you came up onto that stage
after you'd lost...

06:45.452 --> 06:47.978
...and right off the top of your head,
am I right?

06:48.154 --> 06:50.054
You made up that speech on the spot.

06:50.223 --> 06:51.657
He did.

06:52.459 --> 06:55.690
BAKER: I wasn't even on your team
and you made me feel proud.

06:55.862 --> 06:57.762
You made me feel like...

06:57.964 --> 06:59.864
Feel like this country had a purpose.

07:00.667 --> 07:04.365
You made a lot of folks feel like
we had nominated the wrong guy that night.

07:04.537 --> 07:05.834
[CHUCKLES]

07:08.508 --> 07:12.240
You are the best damn performer
I have ever seen in my political career.

07:12.412 --> 07:16.406
Now, maybe you have made a couple of gaffes,
had a couple of bad days...

07:16.583 --> 07:19.883
...but I think it would be a mistake
to keep you on a tight leash...

07:20.053 --> 07:22.579
...and not out in front of big crowds
where you belong.

07:22.756 --> 07:24.520
What are you suggesting, Jim?

07:24.691 --> 07:27.353
We have to accept
Carter's challenge to debate.

07:27.527 --> 07:31.725
No, no, no. We can't afford
any more bloopers and blunders.

07:31.898 --> 07:35.857
- Let people get to know who you really are.
- No, Jim, no. We're down, we're not out.

07:36.035 --> 07:38.504
We sure as hell are going to lose
if we don't take a risk.

07:44.310 --> 07:46.074
So, what do you say, governor?

07:47.113 --> 07:48.808
Think you can handle Jimmy Carter?

07:56.156 --> 07:58.147
[COUNTRY MUSIC PLAYING
OVER SPEAKERS]

08:00.393 --> 08:02.418
JUDGE: Where is everyone?
MAN: Come on.

08:02.595 --> 08:04.927
- President's in town.
- Everyone's on detail, judge.

08:07.967 --> 08:11.267
- Set him right there.
-Illegal possession, Your Honor.

08:11.437 --> 08:13.667
Right hand on the Bible.

08:15.642 --> 08:16.734
- John Hinckley?
- Yes.

08:16.910 --> 08:21.006
Do you swear to tell the truth, the whole truth,
nothing but the truth, so help you God?

08:21.181 --> 08:22.410
Yes, ma'am.

08:22.582 --> 08:25.950
JUDGE:
Son, are these your guns?

08:26.119 --> 08:29.180
- All that yours?
- Yes, sir.

08:29.355 --> 08:32.017
- Were you planning to hijack a plane?
- No, sir. No, I--

08:32.192 --> 08:35.684
- I was just going to sell them.
- These here are now property of the state.

08:36.095 --> 08:38.462
And there's a fine of $50
for concealed weapons...

08:38.865 --> 08:42.698
...plus court fees, amounts to 12.50.

08:42.869 --> 08:44.667
Sixty-two fifty all told, judge.

08:44.838 --> 08:49.275
You now have a permanent criminal record.
I do hope you appreciate that, son.

08:49.442 --> 08:54.107
So if there will be nothing else,
lam gonna be getting on home for supper.

08:54.280 --> 08:56.112
- Good night, judge.
- Good night.

08:56.282 --> 08:57.841
WOMAN: Good night.
- Good night, Millie.

08:58.017 --> 09:00.384
That's it. Here you go.

09:02.155 --> 09:03.645
I can go?

09:03.823 --> 09:05.882
Soon as you pay.

09:06.726 --> 09:08.956
<i>With just one debate
so close to the election...</i>

09:09.128 --> 09:12.462
<i>...it is likely to have an overwhelming influence
on the outcome.</i>

09:12.632 --> 09:16.466
<i>As one Republican campaign official
said today, it is the critical crapshoot...</i>

09:16.636 --> 09:17.660
<i>...for both men.</i>

09:20.874 --> 09:22.899
And then through tax breaks...

09:23.109 --> 09:28.912
...we will automatically induce
the area of job creation in those areas.

09:29.115 --> 09:30.310
BAKER:
Hm.

09:30.483 --> 09:31.507
President Carter.

09:32.151 --> 09:36.179
What Mr. Reagan suggests
is all fine and dandy if Medicare exists.

09:36.356 --> 09:37.824
- Oh...
- But under Mr. Reagan--

09:37.991 --> 09:41.154
- Under Mr. Reagan, it will be abolished.
- Jeez. Oh.

09:41.327 --> 09:45.355
While he was still governor of California,
he campaigned heavily against Medicare.

09:45.531 --> 09:47.056
Ah. There he goes again!

09:47.233 --> 09:51.761
All right, I'm sorry, I'm sorry. It is nonsense.
He is hammering away at me on this.

09:51.938 --> 09:54.532
BAKER: Yes, he has been,
and, yes, President Carter will.

09:54.707 --> 09:57.005
- Well--
- But, governor, your reaction was great.

09:57.176 --> 10:01.079
- Maybe I should just say that at the debate.
- You can't say that in the debate.

10:01.247 --> 10:03.545
- Why not, Rick?
- It's not done.

10:03.716 --> 10:06.549
- Well, maybe it should be.
- Okay, well, let's take a break.

10:06.719 --> 10:09.245
Thank you, governor. You're doing great.

10:09.756 --> 10:13.420
[SIGHING]
Governor, I have this for you.

10:13.593 --> 10:16.563
- What is it?
- Research on all of Carter's positions.

10:16.729 --> 10:19.858
Covers everything from the Soviet Union
to the honey bee industry.

10:20.033 --> 10:21.091
Ronnie?

10:21.267 --> 10:23.292
I'm just gonna borrow him for a second.

10:23.469 --> 10:25.563
Governor, when you have a moment.

10:25.738 --> 10:27.399
Sure thing.

10:28.441 --> 10:31.934
- You all right?
- Oh, yeah, it's just late.

10:32.111 --> 10:34.739
I'm gonna take that for you.

10:34.914 --> 10:37.884
Ronnie, they're coming at you
with too much.

10:38.051 --> 10:39.951
- They're nervous.
- Are you?

10:40.954 --> 10:42.547
I'd be crazy if I wasn't.

10:42.722 --> 10:46.784
But I wanna do this, Mommy.

10:46.960 --> 10:50.260
I mean, I can do this.

10:51.064 --> 10:54.830
This is the part where you say,
"Ronnie, you are right, you can."

10:55.001 --> 10:57.129
- I know, I know. I just--
- Heh-heh.

10:57.303 --> 11:01.001
- Did you change your mind?
- No, it's just we're coming at it so late.

11:01.207 --> 11:03.403
You've got so little time to prepare.

11:03.576 --> 11:06.068
- It-- It--
- You know...

11:06.713 --> 11:11.480
...they have been underestimating us
all our lives.

11:11.651 --> 11:14.120
- It's true.
- Right? In Hollywood.

11:14.287 --> 11:17.985
Then when I ran for governor,
they didn't give us a snowball's chance.

11:18.157 --> 11:19.488
Look how that turned out.

11:19.659 --> 11:22.822
It's the same thing here.

11:22.996 --> 11:24.623
I wanna show them, Mommy.

11:25.765 --> 11:28.928
I just need a chance to speak to the people...

11:29.102 --> 11:30.763
...standing next to Jimmy Carter.

11:30.937 --> 11:33.872
I can do this, I know I can.

11:34.340 --> 11:36.172
But just not without your faith.

11:37.176 --> 11:39.270
Have I got that?

11:40.313 --> 11:41.712
You know you have.

11:41.881 --> 11:43.144
Good.

11:43.316 --> 11:45.808
Because I wanna beat
that little son of a bitch.

11:47.487 --> 11:49.956
Now I'm gonna go see what Ed wants.

11:52.525 --> 11:54.323
Michael.

11:56.629 --> 11:57.994
Yes, Nancy?

11:58.164 --> 12:00.724
- Are you behind this?
- What is it?

12:00.900 --> 12:05.133
A binder crammed with garbage
Ronnie couldn't possible digest in a week.

12:05.304 --> 12:08.035
I believe this was Rick's doing.

12:08.207 --> 12:09.504
He's fired.

12:09.675 --> 12:12.872
- Are--?
- Do it. Now.

12:13.046 --> 12:14.639
Okay.

12:15.982 --> 12:17.381
Rick.

12:17.917 --> 12:22.354
<i>Now, you can rewrite
the lines in motion picture scripts...</i>

12:22.522 --> 12:24.820
<i>...but there's no way...</i>

12:25.525 --> 12:30.588
<i>...that</i> a <i>right-wing Republican
with</i> a <i>20-year record in public affairs...</i>

12:30.797 --> 12:33.892
<i>...his statements on the record,
can change his spots...</i>

12:34.067 --> 12:36.092
MAN:
Here's the .22s I was telling you about.

12:37.303 --> 12:38.498
This is nice.

12:38.671 --> 12:42.107
The <i>issue</i> of peace
and the control of nuclear weapons.

12:42.308 --> 12:44.003
<i>On this great fundamental issue...</i>

12:44.610 --> 12:47.272
<i>mall of the candidates are on one side...</i>

12:47.447 --> 12:50.940
...except that Governor Reagan
<i>is</i> on the other side.

12:51.117 --> 12:53.245
MAN <i>[ON</i> TV]: <i>Back at the White House,
aides were...</i>

12:53.419 --> 12:56.389
It's the Rohm RG-14.
Pretty handy for protection.

12:58.124 --> 13:00.957
WOMAN: Can I change the channel?
- No, you may not.

13:01.127 --> 13:02.356
It's just depressing.

13:02.862 --> 13:06.765
Young lady, you need to learn what happens
when we put soft men like Jimmy Carter...

13:06.933 --> 13:09.402
-...in charge of our government.
- Um...

13:11.037 --> 13:14.405
Yeah, I like this one and the Rohm.

13:14.574 --> 13:17.635
<i>- I'll</i> take both of those.
- You got it.

13:20.113 --> 13:23.913
<i>Mr. Carter knows Governor Reagan possesses
a formidable television personality...</i>

13:24.083 --> 13:25.608
<i>...but he believes that with give-and-take...</i>

13:25.785 --> 13:28.220
<i>"Reagan can be made
to look shallow, unknowledgeahle...</i>

13:28.387 --> 13:31.652
<i>...and, despite recent changes in position,
a man of the right wing.</i>

13:33.292 --> 13:34.726
WOMAN:
Good evening.

13:34.894 --> 13:39.263
I'm Ruth Hinen'eld of the League
of Women Voters Education Fund.

13:39.565 --> 13:41.499
[MUTTERING]

13:41.667 --> 13:42.759
Ronnie?

13:42.935 --> 13:45.905
- Should I leave you be?
- No, I'm so happy you're here, Mommy.

13:46.072 --> 13:47.733
It's standing room only out there.

13:47.907 --> 13:49.636
Everything hinges on this debate.

13:49.809 --> 13:53.973
You know politics, it's just like show business.
You give them a hell of an opening...

13:54.147 --> 13:56.912
...coast for a little while,
then give them a big finale.

13:57.083 --> 13:59.677
- And hopefully run for eight years.
- Yes.

13:59.886 --> 14:01.615
[SIGHING]
I'm gonna go get to my seat.

14:01.787 --> 14:04.813
I think you are more nervous than I am.

14:04.991 --> 14:07.255
- That's how it should be.
- Yeah.

14:08.027 --> 14:09.461
Break a leg.

14:10.163 --> 14:12.393
They're, uh, ready for you at the podium, sir.

14:13.833 --> 14:15.767
- Good luck.
- Ahem.

14:15.935 --> 14:18.597
- It's, "Break a leg," Jim.
- Yes, sir.

14:19.138 --> 14:21.835
HINERFELD: Our moderator is Howard Smith.
- Go get them, governor.

14:22.008 --> 14:24.602
- Break a leg, dutch.
SMITH: Thank you, Mrs. Hinerfeld.

14:24.777 --> 14:27.678
<i>The League of Women Voters
is pleased to welcome...</i>

14:27.847 --> 14:31.181
<i>...to the Cleveland, Ohio,
Convention Center Music Hall...</i>

14:31.350 --> 14:33.216
<i>"President Jimmy Carter...</i>

14:33.419 --> 14:37.117
<i>...the Democratic party's candidate
for reelection to the presidency...</i>

14:37.290 --> 14:39.691
<i>...and Governor Ronald Reagan
of California...</i>

14:39.859 --> 14:42.521
<i>...the Republican party's candidate
for the presidency.</i>

14:42.695 --> 14:44.185
RONALD [ON TV]:
That just isn't true.

14:44.363 --> 14:45.797
<i>It has, I said, delayed...</i>

14:45.965 --> 14:50.527
<i>...the actuarial imbalance failing on us
for just a few years with that increase...</i>

14:50.703 --> 14:52.671
WOMAN: John?
- What?

14:52.838 --> 14:55.364
What are you doing?
You're missing the debate.

14:55.741 --> 14:57.175
Just making a sandwich.

14:57.343 --> 14:59.539
Is he eating again?

15:00.746 --> 15:03.044
Oh, honey, you sure
you wanna watch downstairs?

15:03.216 --> 15:05.947
- Yeah.
MAN: John, wait.

15:06.586 --> 15:08.213
[TV VOLUME DECREASES]

15:10.957 --> 15:12.049
A")! PFOSpects?

15:13.092 --> 15:16.722
- Don't you wanna watch the debate?
- I wanna find out what's going on with you.

15:16.896 --> 15:20.696
Nothing's going on. I am trying.

15:20.866 --> 15:22.561
- I applied.
- Where?

15:22.735 --> 15:26.262
- Jack, maybe now's not a good time.
- I just want some answers.

15:26.472 --> 15:30.568
Whatever happened to your writing career?
You wanted to take that class, right, at Yale?

15:30.743 --> 15:33.235
I paid for it, remember?
What the hell happened?

15:34.013 --> 15:36.880
And what about your plan
to be a bigtime rock 'n' roll star?

15:37.049 --> 15:39.916
WOMAN: Jack.
- Honey, I'm just talking.

15:43.122 --> 15:47.753
You disappear, then show up out of nowhere.
We don't even know where you're going.

15:47.927 --> 15:50.589
- Why don't you--?
- Jo Ann, please.

15:52.265 --> 15:53.790
- John?
- What?

15:54.000 --> 15:56.128
L-- I don't know, Dad.

15:56.702 --> 15:59.603
I'm just-- You wouldn't understand.

15:59.772 --> 16:02.434
I just wanna know
where all this is headed. That's all.

16:03.309 --> 16:06.438
Your mom and I have been-- Can I tell him?

16:06.612 --> 16:08.580
Yeah, I'm just gonna tell him.

16:09.015 --> 16:11.575
We found another therapist.

16:11.751 --> 16:13.879
Actually, he's a psychiatrist.

16:15.621 --> 16:18.056
We'd like you to give him a try.

16:18.624 --> 16:21.525
If I say yes, will you let me go downstairs?

16:22.828 --> 16:24.057
Yes.

16:25.331 --> 16:27.095
Okay.

16:30.736 --> 16:32.568
- So you'll see him?
- Yes.

16:33.839 --> 16:35.170
[REAGAN CHUCKLES ON TV]

16:35.341 --> 16:37.503
<i>There you go again.</i>

16:37.677 --> 16:40.908
When <i>I</i> opposed Medicare,
there was another piece <i>of...</i>

16:41.080 --> 16:43.742
<i>CARTER: For the nation,
here's my plan for the future.</i>

16:43.916 --> 16:47.682
<i>I ask the American people
to join me in this partnership.</i>

16:49.555 --> 16:51.614
<i>REAGAN:
I would like to add my words of thanks...</i>

16:51.791 --> 16:53.987
<i>...to the ladies
of The League of Women Voters...</i>

16:54.160 --> 16:55.855
You talking to me?

16:56.062 --> 16:57.757
<i>...making these debates possible.</i>

16:57.930 --> 16:59.921
You talking to me?
You talking to me?

17:01.367 --> 17:06.999
One day, a real rain's gonna come
and wash away all the scum off the streets.

17:07.873 --> 17:08.999
You talking to me?

17:13.813 --> 17:17.840
Are you better off
than you were four years ago?

17:18.017 --> 17:20.679
<i>Mr. Germond,
your snap impressions of last night.</i>

17:20.853 --> 17:24.790
<i>It was a draw. They were very defensive.
They both have a lotto be defensive about.</i>

17:24.957 --> 17:26.550
<i>And David Broder.</i>

17:26.726 --> 17:28.854
<i>Reagan talked to the country effectively.</i>

17:29.028 --> 17:32.658
<i>Carter talked to his specific constituencies
even more effectively.</i>

17:32.832 --> 17:34.800
<i>How many of you believe that tomorrow...</i>

17:34.967 --> 17:38.597
<i>...we're gonna whip the Republicans
all the way across this nation?</i>

17:38.904 --> 17:41.669
[SHOWER RUNNING]

17:41.841 --> 17:44.173
<i>But the imbalance on the map behind...</i>

17:44.343 --> 17:47.335
<i>...is as striking as I have ever seen it,
working in this studio.</i>

17:47.847 --> 17:48.905
<i>Remarkable.</i>

17:49.115 --> 17:51.812
<i>One state so far called
for a sitting president of the United States.</i>

17:51.984 --> 17:53.918
[PHONE RINGING]

17:54.120 --> 17:55.588
<i>And as I say._._</i>

17:55.755 --> 17:57.189
Hello?

17:59.392 --> 18:01.724
Oh. Oh, yes.

18:01.894 --> 18:04.989
Uh, yes. I'll-- I'll--

18:05.164 --> 18:07.223
Hold on a second.

18:07.400 --> 18:09.164
Ronnie?

18:10.569 --> 18:11.661
Ronnie?

18:11.837 --> 18:13.362
REAGAN:
I'm getting out of the shower.

18:13.539 --> 18:16.372
It's Jimmy Carter on the phone.

18:17.543 --> 18:18.874
What the heck does he want?

18:19.044 --> 18:22.708
- Well, what do you think that he wants?
- No, no, no. It's too early for that.

18:22.882 --> 18:26.546
- The polls aren't even closed.
- You think he cares about the West Coast?

18:28.254 --> 18:30.746
Uh, yes, this is Ron Reagan.

18:32.158 --> 18:34.286
Hello, Mr. President.

18:37.263 --> 18:40.289
Well, thank you, Mr. President.

18:40.800 --> 18:44.896
Well, you put up a good fight,
and I want to assure you...

18:45.070 --> 18:48.267
...that, I and my team, we will--

18:48.441 --> 18:52.878
We will do our level best
to make this a smooth transition.

18:53.612 --> 18:56.809
You too. Good bye.

19:00.820 --> 19:02.948
[SCREAMS]

19:03.122 --> 19:05.113
[BOTH LAUGHING]

19:07.326 --> 19:09.818
Oh! Oh, Ronnie.

19:10.996 --> 19:12.691
MAN:
John?

19:15.734 --> 19:17.327
John.

19:19.271 --> 19:21.103
What? What was the question?

19:21.273 --> 19:24.243
If you couldn't be a musician,
what would you be?

19:24.410 --> 19:28.813
A composer, like John Lennon.

19:30.015 --> 19:31.608
Lennon.

19:32.017 --> 19:35.715
Or, um, Paul McCartney.

19:37.857 --> 19:39.951
More Lennon.

19:40.125 --> 19:42.253
Aim high, right?

19:42.595 --> 19:44.529
And if that doesn't work out?

19:44.730 --> 19:46.630
A writer.

19:46.799 --> 19:48.961
It's kind of my obsession lately.

19:49.134 --> 19:52.866
That and the person I mentioned earlier.

19:53.806 --> 19:56.104
- The actress.
- Mm-hm.

19:57.510 --> 20:00.002
Have you had any luck finding a job?

20:00.179 --> 20:02.204
I don't need a job.

20:02.381 --> 20:04.349
I'm gonna be famous.

20:04.517 --> 20:06.713
- A writer, someday.
- Yeah.

20:06.886 --> 20:09.878
I understand.
Have you at least tried to find a job?

20:10.055 --> 20:11.113
Hm?

20:11.824 --> 20:13.053
[SleHs]

20:13.259 --> 20:15.660
Why don't you just ask my mom and dad?

20:15.828 --> 20:17.887
I'm asking you, John.

20:18.063 --> 20:20.794
It matters because you're the one
who has to take the initiative.

20:20.966 --> 20:22.627
Initiative?

20:22.801 --> 20:24.326
You need direction, John.

20:24.503 --> 20:26.870
Is there some way
you can get to a better place?

20:27.039 --> 20:28.905
You know, a place where you wanna be.

20:29.074 --> 20:33.511
Whatever that is, you're not gonna get there
unless you take action.

20:33.679 --> 20:35.169
JOHN:
Mm-hm.

20:38.284 --> 20:39.718
[ELEVATOR DINGS]

20:43.022 --> 20:46.390
MAN 1 <i>[ON</i> TV]: <i>...until very recently,
I was jogging in Central Park two months ago...</i>

20:46.559 --> 20:50.325
<i>-...and ran into John and Yoko six weeks ago...
Excuse me.</i>

20:53.299 --> 20:56.360
- How do I get to the Blair House?
- What's that?

20:57.570 --> 21:00.505
It's where the president-elect lives.

21:01.240 --> 21:04.369
- The what?
- Just somewhere near the White House.

21:05.244 --> 21:07.440
<i>MAN 7.". All right, Geraldo,
thank you very much, indeed.</i>

21:07.613 --> 21:11.607
<i>What we want to do now is go to Lynn Sherr
who is outside Roosevelt hospital.</i>

21:11.817 --> 21:14.252
<i>Lynn, just bring us up to date, would you?</i>

21:14.420 --> 21:17.685
<i>Under what circumstances
did John Lennon die?</i>

21:17.856 --> 21:21.622
- What happened?
- The White House is on there somewhere.

21:22.227 --> 21:26.130
Someone put a bullet in John Lennon.
Killed him.

21:26.332 --> 21:29.029
LYNN <i>[ON</i> TV]: <i>Got out the limousine
to their apartment at The Dakota...</i>

21:29.201 --> 21:31.568
<i>...where they were shot
by a man described as~</i>

21:33.405 --> 21:35.840
John Lennon is dead.

21:36.241 --> 21:39.108
The world is over.

21:40.079 --> 21:42.980
I don't know why people wanna live.

21:44.850 --> 21:46.443
I still think about Jodie.

21:47.753 --> 21:50.279
She's all I really think about.

21:50.456 --> 21:53.391
That and John Lennon's death.

21:54.393 --> 21:55.451
<i>Blended together.</i>

21:55.628 --> 22:00.065
<i>Mark David Chapman,
the guy who killed Lennon, {just-</i>

22:00.232 --> 22:04.169
<i>lwonder what it's like to be him,
to he famous.</i>

22:04.803 --> 22:08.762
<i>Now Jodie knows who he is.</i>

22:08.941 --> 22:11.103
<i>Someone needs to save her.</i>

22:11.276 --> 22:14.075
Just like Travis Bickle did in Taxi Driver.

22:14.246 --> 22:16.305
[MAKING GUNSHOT NOISES]

22:28.160 --> 22:30.094
<i>Jodie': the only thing that matters...</i>

22:30.696 --> 22:32.425
<i>...and I just want her to know that.</i>

22:33.766 --> 22:35.359
John.

22:35.534 --> 22:37.161
Hi, Mom.

22:40.406 --> 22:42.773
<i>And I don't wanna hurt her.</i>

22:44.410 --> 22:46.606
<i>But sometimes...</i>

22:47.179 --> 22:54.176
...I think that I would just rather see her
not on Earth than with other guys.

22:55.487 --> 22:59.788
<i>And I do not want to stay on this Earth
without her.</i>

22:59.958 --> 23:04.896
So, what do you think, open presents
Christmas Eve or the next morning?

23:05.064 --> 23:07.726
- I just need to find her.
- Don't we usually do morning?

23:07.933 --> 23:10.903
- Talk to her.
- We did that one year, Jack, I think.

23:11.070 --> 23:12.834
But Christmas Eve is a tradition.

23:13.305 --> 23:14.670
Let's do Christmas Eve then.

23:14.840 --> 23:17.741
- In person.
JO ANN: John, what do you think?

23:20.045 --> 23:21.570
Or something.

23:21.947 --> 23:23.244
[TAPE RECORDER CLICKS]

23:32.858 --> 23:35.190
<i>REAGAN:
I, Ronald Reagan, do solemnly swear-</i>

23:35.360 --> 23:39.661
MAN: --that <i>I</i> will faithfully execute
the office of President of the United States-

23:39.832 --> 23:43.496
REAGAN: --that <i>I</i> will faithfully execute
the office of President of the United States-

23:43.669 --> 23:46.036
<i>MAN:
"and will, to the best of my ability-</i>

23:46.205 --> 23:48.071
<i>REAGAN:
"and will, to the best of my ability-</i>

23:48.240 --> 23:51.369
<i>MAN:
“preserve, protect, and defend-</i>

23:51.543 --> 23:53.705
<i>REAGAN:
“preserve, protect, and defend-</i>

23:53.879 --> 23:55.938
<i>MAN:
-the constitution of the United States.</i>

23:56.115 --> 23:58.015
<i>REAGAN:
-the constitution of the United States.</i>

23:58.183 --> 23:59.446
MAN:
So help you God.

23:59.618 --> 24:01.712
REAGAN:
So help me God.

24:08.227 --> 24:09.592
[SleHs]

24:22.608 --> 24:24.076
[CHUCKLES]

24:26.445 --> 24:28.607
Old Resolute.

24:28.781 --> 24:34.652
- We can get you a different one, if you like.
- Oh, no, no, no. This was also Kennedy's desk.

24:35.053 --> 24:36.418
I'm keeping this.

24:39.024 --> 24:41.823
Nancy, see anything you want to change?

24:42.427 --> 24:43.826
Don't get me started.

24:44.897 --> 24:46.729
- Mike, do you have the little--?
- Here.

24:46.899 --> 24:47.923
Thank you.

24:48.400 --> 24:52.598
You who were with me in Sacramento
will recognize this.

24:52.771 --> 24:55.604
Jim, you're the new recruit, but:

24:55.774 --> 24:59.574
"There is no limit to what a man can do
or where he can go...

24:59.745 --> 25:03.113
...if he doesn't mind who gets the credit."

25:03.682 --> 25:06.947
Well, all of you in this room deserve
a lot of that credit...

25:07.119 --> 25:10.089
...for getting us where we are today.

25:12.658 --> 25:14.490
And...

25:15.627 --> 25:18.688
...Nancy, I raise my glass to you.

25:18.864 --> 25:20.423
Sorry I'm late.

25:21.567 --> 25:27.336
Mr. President, Mrs. Reagan,
congratulations. Big day.

25:28.073 --> 25:31.099
- What is this?
- Something the president and I agreed on.

25:31.510 --> 25:33.478
Detailing my duties as Secretary of State.

25:33.879 --> 25:35.347
Which are pretty clear.

25:35.514 --> 25:38.313
Something we agreed on,
I'm just making sure.

25:38.483 --> 25:41.043
It says here
that you would have absolute power...

25:41.220 --> 25:43.450
...over all matters of foreign policy.

25:43.622 --> 25:45.522
- That's right.
BAKER: You can't be serious.

25:45.691 --> 25:47.785
Well, it's all very clear.

25:47.960 --> 25:49.121
It's absurd.

25:49.294 --> 25:50.887
This is hardly the time or place.

25:51.096 --> 25:52.996
.L..
MEESE: Al, this would have to be run...

25:53.165 --> 25:55.497
...by the Joint Chiefs,
the National Security Advisor.

25:55.667 --> 25:57.726
- Weinberger.
BAKER: Secretary of Defense.

25:57.903 --> 25:59.667
HAIG:
The president and I have discussed this.

25:59.838 --> 26:02.068
- You haven't even been confirmed yet.
REAGAN: Al, Al...

26:02.241 --> 26:05.176
...I think we can leave this discussion
until later.

26:05.344 --> 26:08.370
Why don't you grab a glass of champagne?

26:09.815 --> 26:12.341
Hm. Well, thank you.

26:12.517 --> 26:14.576
I'll, um, just leave that with you...

26:14.753 --> 26:19.350
...and, with your permission,
I need to get back to the State Department.

26:20.259 --> 26:21.988
Again, congratulations.

26:26.131 --> 26:28.156
Fella really knows how to kill a party.

26:28.333 --> 26:30.563
[ALL CHUCKLE]

26:31.503 --> 26:33.494
It's getting worse.

26:33.672 --> 26:35.868
That's all I can say.

26:37.676 --> 26:40.407
Do you think that we ought to...?

26:41.346 --> 26:44.509
- Is there some place that he can go that--?
- Jo Ann.

26:45.584 --> 26:47.882
It sounds drastic, but is that an option?

26:48.353 --> 26:50.617
No. No, absolutely not.

26:50.789 --> 26:53.121
I've worked with these treatment centers.

26:53.292 --> 26:58.560
If you go that route, you're just making
an emotional cripple out of him. John is...

26:58.730 --> 27:01.256
Well, to put it bluntly,
John is simply a young man...

27:01.433 --> 27:03.902
-...who has had everything handed to him.
- Heh. Agreed.

27:04.536 --> 27:06.163
I just don't get it, doctor.

27:06.872 --> 27:10.467
Couple years ago, he was just a normal kid.
Did you tell him, John?

27:11.376 --> 27:14.243
He was good at sports,
he was popular with his friends.

27:14.413 --> 27:17.678
You were even president of your class
one year, weren't you, John?

27:18.817 --> 27:19.875
John?

27:22.421 --> 27:24.446
Yeah. Yeah. Yes.

27:26.091 --> 27:28.185
- And then, bam, all of a sudden.
- Look...

27:28.994 --> 27:31.656
...the three of you need to make a contract.

27:31.830 --> 27:34.765
John, are you listening?
You need to be more responsible.

27:34.933 --> 27:38.767
Get a job and take control,
and stop manipulating your parents.

27:38.937 --> 27:44.899
Mom, Dad, your job is not to bend.

27:45.844 --> 27:47.903
Can we all agree to that?

27:54.987 --> 27:56.716
JO ANN:
John?

27:58.457 --> 27:59.947
Okay.

28:00.125 --> 28:02.116
MAN 1: Mr. President!
MAN 2: Mr. President, what can--?

28:02.394 --> 28:04.488
REAGAN: Mark.
- President Reagan, during your campaign...

28:04.663 --> 28:08.793
...there was talk about scrapping SALT <i>ll</i>
and bringing the Soviets back to the table.

28:08.967 --> 28:10.935
Is that something you plan to do now?

28:11.103 --> 28:15.040
Well, I don't know about that,
but, uh, I can say this.

28:15.240 --> 28:21.179
I know of no leader of the Soviet Union,
including the present leadership...

28:21.346 --> 28:26.978
...that hasn't made it their goal
to promote a one-world communist state.

28:27.152 --> 28:32.318
The only morality they recognize
is that which will further their cause.

28:32.491 --> 28:35.825
Meaning they reserve the right
to commit any crime...

28:35.994 --> 28:39.055
...to lie, to cheat, to attain that.

28:39.264 --> 28:41.062
- Mr. President!
- Mr. President!

28:41.266 --> 28:44.668
Now, does that mean in your view
that détente is even possible?

28:44.836 --> 28:46.736
Well, détente, uh--

28:46.905 --> 28:51.467
Détente has been a one-way street,
and we have been on the losing end.

28:51.643 --> 28:53.475
I'll leave it at that. Thank you.

28:53.645 --> 28:55.477
MAN 3: Mr. President!
- That's all.

28:55.647 --> 28:58.639
- Have you spoken to President Brezhnev?
MAN 4: Mr. President!

28:58.817 --> 28:59.875
Mr. President!

29:00.052 --> 29:04.353
Heh-heh. Now, Dick, the Russians do lie,
cheat and steal, don't they?

29:04.523 --> 29:07.515
- They certainly do, Mr. President.
- Heh-heh.

29:07.692 --> 29:10.184
I think the buttered popcorn is perfect,
don't you?

29:10.362 --> 29:11.989
Oh, trust me, it's the cream.

29:12.164 --> 29:13.222
Really?

29:13.398 --> 29:15.924
Oh, popcorn yellow
would be malpractice to me.

29:16.101 --> 29:20.060
- Heh-heh.
- George. Mommy, Ted, how's it coming?

29:20.238 --> 29:25.438
For a remodel of one of the most venerated
houses on the face of the planet, not too bad.

29:25.610 --> 29:27.874
I'm sorry for all the mess, sweetheart.

29:28.046 --> 29:30.242
Well, can't make an omelet... Heh.

29:30.415 --> 29:32.406
- Tomorrow morning then.
<i>- I'll</i> see you then.

29:32.584 --> 29:34.279
Mr. President.

29:34.453 --> 29:36.217
Did you see this morning's clippings?

29:36.721 --> 29:39.850
Oh, why do you read these?

29:40.025 --> 29:41.515
Not for pleasure, that's for sure.

29:41.693 --> 29:42.956
[SleHs]

29:43.128 --> 29:44.289
Why are they so mean to me?

29:44.463 --> 29:47.262
Why are they so mean to anyone?
Sells papers.

29:47.432 --> 29:50.868
There's an article that goes on and on
about the fact that I own a gun...

29:51.036 --> 29:54.734
...which is something that I casually mentioned
off the record to ajournalist.

29:54.906 --> 29:58.308
There's this one, calls me a "dragon lady."

29:58.477 --> 30:01.606
I don't understand it.
I cheerfully agree to do these interviews...

30:01.780 --> 30:05.239
...I'm as open as I can be,
and they tear me to pieces.

30:05.417 --> 30:08.876
I certainly hope that your people
are doing a better job protecting you...

30:09.054 --> 30:10.988
...than they are protecting me.

30:11.156 --> 30:15.821
These were all classified, completely
unavailable to us before the election.

30:15.994 --> 30:18.725
Look on page five, look on page nine.

30:19.865 --> 30:21.333
They're summaries.

30:21.500 --> 30:24.492
The Soviets are in much worse
economic shape than we ever thought.

30:24.669 --> 30:26.228
I think...

30:26.404 --> 30:28.805
...if we do something now, we can win.

30:28.974 --> 30:31.170
Win? Win what?

30:31.376 --> 30:35.973
The Cold War. If we act fast, hit them hard
before they know what happened.

30:36.148 --> 30:38.674
- But we can't just outspend them.
- Why not?

30:38.884 --> 30:42.445
Because our economy is on the verge
of another recession. It's sick.

30:42.621 --> 30:44.487
The Democrats are saying it, the press...

30:44.656 --> 30:46.852
- Who cares?
- We can't spend money we don't have.

30:47.025 --> 30:50.859
If we keep spending,
we'll be worse off than the Russians.

30:51.029 --> 30:55.694
I disagree. You've got the Russians
in Afghanistan, the solidarity movement.

30:55.901 --> 30:57.665
Who knows what the hell will happen there?

30:57.836 --> 31:00.965
Intel is pointing to a lot of movement
inside Polish borders...

31:01.139 --> 31:03.608
...with a possible intervention by Russia.

31:03.775 --> 31:07.541
Mr. President, we cannot wait.
The time to act is now.

31:07.712 --> 31:11.205
We outspend the Soviets on defense,
we win.

31:11.416 --> 31:13.612
STOCKMAN: Mr. President,
forget the Russians for now.

31:13.785 --> 31:17.688
Our focus should be on the economy.

31:17.856 --> 31:20.018
That's the priority.

31:20.659 --> 31:24.687
Well, David, Richard, thank you very much.

31:24.863 --> 31:26.331
Let us discuss this.

31:26.498 --> 31:28.466
- Thank you, Mr. President.
- Thank you.

31:28.633 --> 31:30.192
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

31:31.303 --> 31:34.238
David. Richard. Thank you.

31:37.676 --> 31:41.670
Well, you fellas know what I want.

31:42.214 --> 31:44.080
Let's make it happen.

31:49.854 --> 31:51.344
[LINE RINGING]

31:54.059 --> 31:55.185
WOMAN [OVER PHONE]:
Hello?

31:55.360 --> 31:56.987
Jodie, hi.

31:57.162 --> 31:58.755
<i>Who's this?</i>

31:58.964 --> 32:02.059
- It's John Hinckley.
- Who?

32:02.234 --> 32:04.828
L-- I just need to talk to you, okay?

32:05.003 --> 32:07.404
<i>Yeah, well, I don't know you.</i>

32:08.573 --> 32:10.439
Did you get my letters?

32:10.609 --> 32:11.735
No. I- <i>I</i> don't know.

32:11.910 --> 32:14.242
<i>Listen, I gotta go to dinner...</i>

32:14.412 --> 32:17.006
<i>...and I'm not supposed to talk
to people I don't know.</i>

32:17.182 --> 32:18.343
Well, I know you, l..

32:18.516 --> 32:20.883
<i>Look, I don't wanna be mean.</i>

32:21.052 --> 32:25.387
<i>This upsets my roommates when you call,
and it upsets me.</i>

32:25.557 --> 32:27.548
Goodbye.

32:27.726 --> 32:29.353
[TONE HUMMING]

32:30.195 --> 32:31.424
Hello?

32:38.703 --> 32:40.102
[EXHALES]

32:56.921 --> 32:58.116
[GRUNTING]

33:03.828 --> 33:05.922
[CLICKING]

33:07.632 --> 33:08.793
[EXHALES]

33:33.591 --> 33:36.026
WOMAN 1: The party is
after the midterm on Saturday.

33:36.194 --> 33:37.320
He studies in here.

33:37.495 --> 33:39.520
Never mind, don't even ask me about it.

33:39.698 --> 33:40.790
WOMAN 2:
That's okay.

33:40.965 --> 33:43.764
I was running to get here, but--

33:43.935 --> 33:46.563
WOMAN 3:50 you guys would think,
all the things you learn...

33:48.473 --> 33:49.941
Jodie.

33:50.108 --> 33:51.872
JODIE: So embarrassed
by just one little thing that...

33:52.077 --> 33:53.306
JOHN:
Jodie.

33:53.478 --> 33:56.038
MAN: You know her?
- Don't even-- Never mind. Don't even ask.

33:56.214 --> 33:58.205
You know Jodie Foster?

34:00.352 --> 34:01.786
She's my girlfriend.

34:02.654 --> 34:05.385
Heh-heh. Yeah, uh, right.

34:12.130 --> 34:15.896
I know I asked for this, but he has got me
meeting two to three Democrats a day.

34:16.101 --> 34:18.661
- They have no sense of humor.
MEESE: That's for sure.

34:19.237 --> 34:22.467
I met with Leon Panetta
and our California boys last week.

34:22.873 --> 34:24.739
Just a matter of time before they turn.

34:24.909 --> 34:27.206
Well, if you need me to call,
just let me know.

34:27.379 --> 34:29.473
I'm afraid that's going to still leave us...

34:29.647 --> 34:33.708
...a whole chunk of votes short
of passing this economic recovery bill.

34:33.885 --> 34:35.375
Well, what is the latest count?

34:35.553 --> 34:37.248
- What is it, 25?
- Twenty-six.

34:37.422 --> 34:39.322
BAKER:
Twenty-six votes short in the house.

34:39.491 --> 34:42.755
MEESE: It's that darn Tip O'Neill.
He just won't let up.

34:42.927 --> 34:45.259
Accusing us of soaking the poor,
helping the rich.

34:45.429 --> 34:48.661
O'Neill knows how to use the press
to his advantage, that's for sure.

34:48.833 --> 34:51.893
And the press is not exactly warm
to your plan, Mr. President.

34:52.070 --> 34:54.835
- Well, we knew that would be a challenge.
- Mm.

34:55.005 --> 34:58.442
Still, we need to pass this bill.
It is crucial that we do.

34:58.643 --> 35:00.634
Foreign policy is at a stand-still.

35:01.012 --> 35:04.448
Now you've got this whole situation
with the Soviets and Poland.

35:04.649 --> 35:08.552
This bill doesn't go through,
I'm afraid it's more than just this bill...

35:08.720 --> 35:11.018
-...that we're going to lose.
- Well, how do you mean?

35:11.589 --> 35:14.354
Well, Democrats smell blood,
they go right in for the kill.

35:14.526 --> 35:16.551
And, sir, they get tougher
than a rat in an outhouse.

35:16.728 --> 35:17.752
[CHUCKLES]

35:17.929 --> 35:20.023
Point is, who wins this battle...

35:20.198 --> 35:22.690
...shows everyone in this damn town
who's on top...

35:22.867 --> 35:26.201
...who's in charge
for the whole rest of your term.

35:28.406 --> 35:30.465
Understood.

35:32.043 --> 35:34.478
JODIE [OVER PHONE]: Hello?
- Hi. Hi, Jodie.

35:34.679 --> 35:36.875
<i>- Who is this?
- It's John.</i>

35:37.048 --> 35:40.245
- John- Oh, no.
- What's the matter?

35:40.418 --> 35:42.045
<i>- John Hendricks?
- No.</i>

35:42.220 --> 35:44.484
- Hinckley.
- Yes, Hinckley.

35:44.689 --> 35:47.283
<i>Listen, you understand
this is dangerous, right?</i>

35:47.459 --> 35:49.894
<i>And it's not~ It's not fair. It's rude.</i>

35:50.061 --> 35:53.622
I'm not dangerous. I promise.

35:55.233 --> 35:58.635
- Are you having a party?
- No, we're trying to get some sleep.

35:58.803 --> 36:01.397
Do me a favor and <i>don't call</i> back, okay?

36:01.573 --> 36:04.270
So you just don't want me
to ever call you again?

36:04.442 --> 36:06.672
<i>No, but it's been really nice talking to you.</i>

36:06.845 --> 36:09.143
Well, how about just tomorrow?

36:09.314 --> 36:11.305
[TONE HUMMING]

36:13.918 --> 36:15.283
[BANGING NOISE]

36:17.021 --> 36:19.752
<i>REAGAN". During recent weeks,
many of you have asked...</i>

36:19.924 --> 36:22.916
...what can you do
to make America strong again.

36:23.094 --> 36:26.530
I urge you again to contact
your senators and congressmen.

36:26.731 --> 36:30.224
Tell them of your support
for this bipartisan proposal.

36:30.635 --> 36:33.764
Tell them you believe
this is an unequaled opportunity...

36:33.938 --> 36:38.136
...to make government again
the servant of the people.

36:38.309 --> 36:41.006
Thank you and good night.

36:41.179 --> 36:42.476
And we're out.

36:42.647 --> 36:44.046
It was great, guys, thanks.

36:44.516 --> 36:45.642
That was terrific.

36:45.817 --> 36:48.252
Yeah. Jim.

36:49.153 --> 36:50.279
BAKER:
Right on target, sir.

36:50.455 --> 36:53.186
- Mommy, how did that look?
NANCY: Flawless.

36:53.358 --> 36:55.156
BAKER:
It's just that we can't let up.

36:55.326 --> 36:58.489
- No, no, right, more to do, understood.
- What's next?

36:58.663 --> 37:01.462
I've got a few speaking engagements lined up,
mostly unions.

37:01.633 --> 37:02.964
- Good.
- Working class folks.

37:03.134 --> 37:06.069
Well, that's my cup of tea, Jim.
I'm a union man from way back.

37:06.271 --> 37:11.038
- President of the Screen Actors Guild.
- Oh, I know, but these are hard sorts.

37:11.209 --> 37:14.372
They toe the union line.
A lot of them probably didn't vote for you.

37:14.546 --> 37:17.243
Well, we'll just have to change their minds,
won't we? Heh-heh.

37:17.415 --> 37:21.374
Yes, sir. Also, I'm obliged to tell you
that the new approval ratings just came out.

37:21.553 --> 37:24.250
- Ah. Pretty low, are they?
- I'm afraid so.

37:24.422 --> 37:27.357
Democrats have been pretty successful
at hammering away at you.

37:27.525 --> 37:30.153
Jim, I trust you.

37:31.029 --> 37:33.521
Just tell me what to do.

37:33.998 --> 37:36.092
MEESE: That's what I'm saying, Jim.
- See you upstairs.

37:36.301 --> 37:38.770
- A little honey goes a long way.
- Jim?

37:38.937 --> 37:40.427
Yes, ma'am.

37:40.605 --> 37:43.438
If you want the best out of him,
you're going about it the wrong way.

37:43.608 --> 37:45.406
- I'm sorry?
- You're tearing him down.

37:45.577 --> 37:46.772
Uh, no, ma'am, I'm not--

37:46.945 --> 37:49.846
Send him where you want
to whoever you want.

37:50.014 --> 37:53.541
You can even tell him
exactly what it is you need him to say.

37:54.385 --> 37:57.013
But don't tell him that he's failing.

38:00.525 --> 38:03.222
<i>Hello, I'm Tip O'Neill, Speaker of the House.</i>

38:03.394 --> 38:06.022
<i>I, too, just watched
the president of the United States.</i>

38:06.197 --> 38:08.723
<i>And I must agree, he's a super salesman.</i>

38:08.900 --> 38:11.767
<i>He and I don't agree on his plan whatsoever.</i>

38:11.936 --> 38:15.236
<i>I believe in the plan of fairness.
Very easy to put the question.</i>

38:15.406 --> 38:16.805
<i>The question is this:</i>

38:16.975 --> 38:20.468
<i>Do you make over $50,000
or less than $50,000?</i>

38:20.645 --> 38:24.377
<i>If you make over $50,000,
then you're for the Republican plan...</i>

38:24.549 --> 38:26.313
<i>"because that's who it's geared for.</i>

38:26.584 --> 38:28.211
[SIRENS WAILING IN DISTANCE]

38:28.386 --> 38:30.616
WOMAN:
Rest in peace, John.

38:36.494 --> 38:38.553
Lennon's gone.

38:39.897 --> 38:41.058
Yeah, stay cool.

38:41.232 --> 38:43.132
Give peace a chance, huh?

38:43.301 --> 38:44.928
Okay.

38:47.138 --> 38:48.230
WOMAN:
Yeah, well...

38:48.406 --> 38:50.807
- Can I have this, please?
MAN: Hey, it's cool.

38:52.176 --> 38:54.110
My name is John.

38:54.278 --> 38:55.677
Uh-huh.

39:00.184 --> 39:02.516
I've never done this before.

39:03.121 --> 39:06.614
Well, it's 30 bucks for half and half.

39:06.791 --> 39:08.987
- Twenty bucks if you--
- No.

39:09.827 --> 39:13.024
I've never done any of this before.

39:13.898 --> 39:15.525
Okay.

39:20.138 --> 39:24.132
So, John, you wanna do this?

39:25.309 --> 39:29.769
You look exactly like someone I know.

39:36.654 --> 39:40.522
JACK [OVER PHONE]: Hello?
- Dad, it's John.

39:40.692 --> 39:43.821
- Where are you now?
- I'm in New York.

39:44.862 --> 39:46.694
I'm broke.

39:47.165 --> 39:49.827
Can you please send me some money?

39:51.436 --> 39:53.461
I wanna come home.

39:58.009 --> 39:59.704
MAN:
Can I get by?

40:07.485 --> 40:09.681
Hey, thanks for picking me up.

40:10.588 --> 40:11.817
You eaten?

40:12.724 --> 40:17.321
Yeah, uh, before I left,
and again on the plane.

40:20.331 --> 40:21.856
What's that?

40:22.366 --> 40:24.528
Antifreeze. Where'd you go this time?

40:25.069 --> 40:27.060
Yale, to check out my writing classes.

40:28.005 --> 40:30.497
You were supposed
to have a job by now, John.

40:33.377 --> 40:36.836
You haven't lived up
to your end of our agreement, John.

40:38.049 --> 40:41.075
Your mom and I,
we had another talk with Dr. Hopper and...

40:42.687 --> 40:45.281
[MAN SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY
OVER PA]

40:48.860 --> 40:50.988
This is for your car.

40:51.429 --> 40:54.888
It's in the parking lot, and it's cold out there.

40:55.767 --> 41:00.227
Second level, um, number 128.

41:03.241 --> 41:05.437
Here's $200.

41:11.949 --> 41:13.644
You're on your own.

41:14.519 --> 41:16.886
- Dad.
- You understand?

41:19.157 --> 41:21.751
Yeah. Yes.

41:25.163 --> 41:26.961
Okay, then.

41:28.733 --> 41:30.167
Dad.

41:33.171 --> 41:37.540
I just wanna thank you
for everything you've done for me.

41:41.279 --> 41:43.748
And, uh, tell Mom--

42:17.582 --> 42:19.209
MAN <i>[on T\/]:
In the first 100 days of a term...</i>

42:19.383 --> 42:22.375
<i>...a president is usually accorded
a honeymoon period.</i>

42:22.587 --> 42:24.055
<i>Not so for Ronald Reagan...</i>

42:24.222 --> 42:27.817
<i>...who faces steep opposition
to his controversial economic programs.</i>

42:27.992 --> 42:29.960
<i>Many critics have even accused
the president...</i>

42:30.127 --> 42:34.121
<i>...of trying to dismantle Roosevelt's legacy
from the New Deal.</i>

42:34.298 --> 42:36.494
And what have you got today, Mommy?

42:36.667 --> 42:39.466
An event for an art museum,
and then Ted later.

42:39.637 --> 42:41.036
We've ordered the china.

42:41.205 --> 42:43.230
Oh, that sounds so great.

42:43.407 --> 42:46.069
- And what about you?
- Well, I'm about to find out.

42:46.244 --> 42:47.837
- Heh-heh.
<i>- I'll</i> see you tonight.

42:50.181 --> 42:51.649
- Good morning.
- Morning, sir.

42:51.816 --> 42:53.807
Good morning, Mr. President.

42:54.652 --> 42:55.710
Thank you, colonel.

42:55.887 --> 42:59.255
Big event today is your speech
to the AFL-CIO.

42:59.423 --> 43:02.188
And this morning,
we've got you thanking Hispanic leaders.

43:02.360 --> 43:04.988
- It'll be quick, it's just a photo op.
- Good.

43:20.211 --> 43:22.942
[SIGHING]
Plan of attack.

43:24.015 --> 43:28.919
Take the bus to New Haven and kill Jodie.

43:30.421 --> 43:32.446
Kill myself.

43:32.957 --> 43:35.551
Kill myself in front of Jodie.

43:35.726 --> 43:38.423
Kill Jodie and myself.

43:39.897 --> 43:42.366
Assassinate the president.

43:43.768 --> 43:46.203
Just-- Just end it.

43:46.370 --> 43:48.668
End this hell.

43:49.440 --> 43:51.204
Just end it.

43:51.375 --> 43:53.400
REAGAN:
Good morning, Chancellor Schmidt.

43:53.577 --> 43:56.672
Or should I say good afternoon?

43:57.815 --> 44:00.785
I was very sorry to hear about your father.

44:01.285 --> 44:03.720
Well, I lost my mom years ago...

44:03.888 --> 44:08.189
...but there's not a day that goes by
that I don't think of her.

44:08.793 --> 44:13.959
I take it you know about the latest development
with the Soviets.

44:15.099 --> 44:19.400
Well, our intelligence says
they are making movements inside of Poland.

44:20.304 --> 44:23.069
The more this solidarity movement
shows its teeth...

44:23.240 --> 44:25.766
...the more brazen Brezhnev gets.

44:28.612 --> 44:32.014
JOHN: <i>Dear Jodie, there is</i> a <i>definite possibility...</i>

44:32.216 --> 44:35.083
<i>...that I will be killed
in my attempt to get Reagan.</i>

44:35.252 --> 44:38.688
<i>It is for this very reason
that I am writing you this letter now.</i>

44:38.856 --> 44:42.724
<i>As you well know by now,
I love you very much.</i>

45:01.946 --> 45:06.281
Over the past seven months, <i>I</i> have left you
dozens of poems, letters and love messages...

45:06.450 --> 45:09.112
<i>...in</i> the faint hope
that you could develop an interest <i>in</i> me.

45:09.487 --> 45:11.546
<i>Although we talked on the phone...</i>

45:11.756 --> 45:15.283
<i>...I</i> never had the nerve to simply approach you
and introduce myself.

45:15.459 --> 45:20.659
<i>Besides my shyness, I honestly did not wish
to bother you with my constant presence.</i>

45:20.831 --> 45:24.995
<i>I know the many messages left at your door
and in your mailbox were a nuisance...</i>

45:25.169 --> 45:28.969
<i>...but I felt that it was the most painless way
for me to express my love for you.</i>

45:30.374 --> 45:33.571
<i>I feel very good about the fact
that you at least know my name...</i>

45:33.778 --> 45:35.473
<i>...and know how Heel about you...</i>

45:35.646 --> 45:37.637
<i>...and by hanging around your dormitory...</i>

45:37.815 --> 45:42.082
<i>...I've come to realize that I am the topic
of more than a little conversation.</i>

45:43.921 --> 45:47.084
- Good morning, George.
- Good morning, Mrs. Reagan.

45:48.359 --> 45:49.986
Is everything all right?

45:50.161 --> 45:51.925
It's fine.

45:53.397 --> 45:55.195
Can you tell Mommy?

45:55.866 --> 45:58.233
Tell Mommy I gotta go.

45:58.402 --> 45:59.870
All right?

46:00.037 --> 46:02.665
Okay, bye-bye-

46:02.840 --> 46:05.673
- Ready to go to the Hilton?
- Yeah.

46:08.212 --> 46:10.544
REAGAN: Hi, Tim.
- Afternoon, sir.

46:10.714 --> 46:12.113
Good afternoon, Ray.

46:12.716 --> 46:14.445
Good to see you. Hey, Jerry.

46:14.618 --> 46:16.108
Afternoon, Mr. President.

46:16.320 --> 46:17.845
Thank you.

46:18.923 --> 46:22.917
Rawhide in, ready to roll.

46:23.094 --> 46:28.555
JOHN: <i>However full of ridicule it may be,</i>
at <i>least you know that I'll always love you.</i>

46:28.732 --> 46:33.135
<i>Jodie, I would abandon this idea
of getting Reagan in a second...</i>

46:33.337 --> 46:36.967
<i>...if I could only win your heart
and live out the rest of my life with you.</i>

46:37.141 --> 46:38.506
[ALL CHEERING]

46:38.809 --> 46:40.743
[SIREN FADES]

46:41.779 --> 46:42.837
Rawhide's arriving.

46:51.255 --> 46:52.950
MAN 1:
President Reagan!

46:53.124 --> 46:56.492
MAN 2: Mr. President, would you care
to comment on the events in Poland?

46:56.660 --> 46:59.129
MAN 3:
Thattaway, President Reagan!

47:01.565 --> 47:03.397
MAN 2:
Mr. President, anything, please.

47:03.567 --> 47:05.228
MAN 4:
Did they fail, sir?

47:05.402 --> 47:06.563
WOMAN:
I love you!

47:06.737 --> 47:08.501
MAN 5:
Let's go over this way, please, sir.

47:08.672 --> 47:13.303
Let's mark this as three and a half feet.
Let's see...

47:13.477 --> 47:15.411
- Hello, Ted.
- Well, hello.

47:15.579 --> 47:17.980
- We weren't expecting you till much later.
- I know.

47:18.149 --> 47:21.175
I was feeling funny.
I decided to come home early.

47:21.385 --> 47:23.820
- George, thank you. I'm good for now.
- Yes, ma'am.

47:23.988 --> 47:28.357
- Are you sick?
- No, just an oddish sensation.

47:28.526 --> 47:32.861
- Do you want us to leave?
- No, no. Let's, uh-- Let's get to work.

47:33.030 --> 47:35.658
Maybe it'll take my mind off it,
whatever it is.

47:35.833 --> 47:40.327
Now, tell me what your thoughts are
about this room.

47:40.504 --> 47:44.839
REAGAN: There has been a lot of talk
in the last several weeks here.

47:46.510 --> 47:50.447
JOHN: <i>I will admit to you that the reason
I'm going ahead with this attempt now...</i>

47:50.614 --> 47:54.778
<i>...is because I just cannot wait any longer
to impress you.</i>

47:56.320 --> 48:00.780
<i>I've got to do something now
to make you understand in no uncertain terms...</i>

48:00.958 --> 48:04.724
<i>...that I am doing all of this for your sake.</i>

48:05.696 --> 48:08.222
- What about these things here?
- That is the challenge.

48:08.432 --> 48:11.026
- Awful.
-"Awful" is the word. Heh.

48:11.835 --> 48:15.738
JOHN: <i>By sacrificing my freedom
and possibly my life...</i>

48:15.940 --> 48:18.170
<i>...I hope to change your mind about me.</i>

48:18.342 --> 48:20.470
MAN 1: Hey, he's here.
Hey, I gotta get this shot.

48:20.644 --> 48:24.638
<i>This letter is being written only an hour
before I leave for the Hilton hotel.</i>

48:24.815 --> 48:26.874
MAN 2:
It's him! He's coming!

48:27.051 --> 48:28.712
[ALL CHEERING]

48:28.886 --> 48:30.251
MAN 3:
All right, he's in position.

48:31.322 --> 48:34.553
<i>Jodie, I'm asking you
to please look into your heart...</i>

48:34.725 --> 48:36.318
- You deal with the press.
- Got it.

48:36.493 --> 48:40.487
<i>...and at least give me the chance
with this historical deed...</i>

48:40.664 --> 48:43.531
<i>...to gain your respect and love.</i>

48:43.901 --> 48:45.391
<i>I</i> love you forever.

48:48.172 --> 48:49.196
Whoa!

48:49.373 --> 48:50.431
<i>John Hinckley.</i>

48:50.608 --> 48:52.576
[CROWD SCREAMING]

48:53.677 --> 48:54.974
Get inside!

48:57.748 --> 48:59.045
Crazy, I got him!

49:01.118 --> 49:02.586
Get him out of here!

49:02.753 --> 49:05.222
AGENT 1: Hold him down!
AGENT 2: Get the car out of here!

49:05.389 --> 49:08.791
- Haul ass, haul ass, let's go! Go!
AGENT 1: Get him out!

49:08.993 --> 49:11.052
Stay down, Mr. President.

49:14.298 --> 49:16.460
AGENT 2: Hold him down!
AGENT 3: Where's the gun?

49:16.634 --> 49:19.467
- Get the goddamn car!
AGENT 3: Where's his weapon?

49:19.637 --> 49:24.768
- Where's the goddamn weapon?
- Anyone got a handkerchief, a handkerchief?

49:24.942 --> 49:26.706
- Stay there, don't move.
- Here you go.

49:26.877 --> 49:28.572
You'll be all right. You'll be fine.

49:28.746 --> 49:30.236
We're going to crown!

49:30.414 --> 49:32.473
I got him. Breathe.

49:32.650 --> 49:34.584
Stay with us, Tim. You're okay.

49:34.752 --> 49:37.312
- What's wrong with you?
- Stay down! Stay down!

49:38.389 --> 49:39.413
[GRUNTING]

49:39.590 --> 49:42.992
JERRY: Rawhide's okay.
Stagecoach rolling to crown.

49:43.160 --> 49:44.252
WOMAN:
<i>Roger</i> that, Stagecoach.

49:44.428 --> 49:46.123
JERRY: Are you hit?
- Damn it, Jerry.

49:46.297 --> 49:47.890
I think you broke one of my ribs.

49:48.065 --> 49:49.260
Stay down!

49:49.433 --> 49:51.094
- You got his arm?
- Don't move.

49:51.268 --> 49:53.760
- Who do you think you are?
- Stay there, stay there.

49:53.937 --> 49:55.735
We need a patrol car.

49:55.906 --> 49:59.171
- Don't move.
- Get us-- Get us a marked unit.

50:00.244 --> 50:01.837
Come on.

50:02.046 --> 50:03.138
It won't open!

50:03.314 --> 50:05.783
Hey! Let's take him over here.

50:09.186 --> 50:11.678
JOHN: Ungh!
- Get in and shut up.

50:15.559 --> 50:17.152
I think you broke my wrist.

50:17.328 --> 50:19.990
You're lucky
that's the only thing that's broken.

50:20.631 --> 50:22.565
Headquarters.

50:23.133 --> 50:24.191
[SIREN CHIRPS]

50:24.368 --> 50:26.336
[GROANING]

50:26.503 --> 50:29.495
I'm having a hard time breathing.

50:29.673 --> 50:32.142
[COUGHING]

50:32.309 --> 50:34.209
JERRY:
Yeah. Easy.

50:37.381 --> 50:40.351
I think you might have broke it.
You might have punctured a lung.

50:40.517 --> 50:43.646
Uh, let's get to the hospital.
Change of course.

50:43.821 --> 50:45.721
Here, here, here.

50:45.889 --> 50:47.948
G. W. Hospital now!

50:48.125 --> 50:50.355
- Let's go!
DRIVER: Roger that.

50:50.527 --> 50:51.619
Sir.

50:51.795 --> 50:53.559
[CROWD CLAMORING]

50:53.731 --> 50:56.166
MAN 1:
Where's that ambulance?

50:56.333 --> 50:58.199
MAN 2:
How's he doing?

51:00.371 --> 51:02.863
Hey, you, medic! Get him over here!

51:03.040 --> 51:05.338
REPORTER:
I do not know where they've taken him.

51:05.509 --> 51:07.978
MAN 1:
Where's the other ambulance?

51:09.246 --> 51:11.374
That's it, Jim, stay still.

51:14.685 --> 51:17.814
Shots were fired.
The president is okay, but shots were fired.

51:17.988 --> 51:19.319
What are you talking about?

51:19.490 --> 51:22.516
A shooting at the Hilton.
It's all over the television.

51:23.727 --> 51:30.064
<i>We understand that at least three persons
have been hit, but we are informed by a-</i>

51:30.234 --> 51:31.565
I need point five epi.

51:31.735 --> 51:33.863
[INDISTINCT RADIO CHATTER]

51:34.037 --> 51:36.199
Can you turn that down, please?

51:36.373 --> 51:39.934
- Officer down at the Hilton--
- That's the White House phone. They always--

51:40.144 --> 51:41.634
Hello?

51:47.084 --> 51:50.520
Mrs. Reagan, there's been a shooting.

51:50.687 --> 51:53.088
Your husband has not been injured,
he is okay.

51:53.257 --> 51:54.588
Others have been shot.

51:54.758 --> 51:57.921
The president is on the way
to George Washington Hospital now, okay?

51:58.095 --> 52:00.792
George, why would he go to the hospital
if he wasn't hurt?

52:00.964 --> 52:04.525
Ma'am, I can't figure that out.
I think he's making sure everyone else is okay.

52:04.701 --> 52:05.964
I'm going to that hospital.

52:06.170 --> 52:08.104
- You can't do that, ma'am.
- Get me my car.

52:08.272 --> 52:11.264
- It's too dangerous, Mrs. Reagan.
- Get me my car, or I will walk.

52:11.442 --> 52:14.412
Rainbow on the move. Listen to me.
This is too dangerous.

52:14.578 --> 52:16.979
There's a train wreck coming.
I need everybody out of here.

52:17.181 --> 52:20.583
If they can go to the unit, take them.
If they can go home, get them home.

52:20.751 --> 52:24.881
- Those kids back there, I want them up to Peds.
COP: ER is being evacuated.

52:25.055 --> 52:27.046
[SIRENS WAILING]

52:31.428 --> 52:33.897
Let's go, let's go. Let's move.

52:34.298 --> 52:36.323
- Come on, Mr. President.
- That's all right.

52:36.500 --> 52:39.162
It's gonna be okay, sir.

52:39.336 --> 52:41.703
- You good?
- Yeah.

52:43.841 --> 52:45.900
- What happened?
- He might have punctured a lung.

52:46.076 --> 52:47.100
Where are we headed?

52:47.277 --> 52:50.406
- Are you having trouble breathing?
- Yeah. Having a hard time breathing.

52:50.581 --> 52:52.606
Okay, come on right this way.

52:52.783 --> 52:54.649
- Easy.
- Let's go left.

52:54.818 --> 52:56.616
- I can't breathe.
WOMAN 1: Whoa!

52:56.787 --> 52:59.950
Get him up. It may be a cardiac.
Let's get him on a gurney.

53:00.123 --> 53:02.148
Over there, second bay.

53:02.326 --> 53:05.455
- Guys, clear out!
- We're going to the second bay on the left.

53:05.629 --> 53:07.620
Get me Labs and get me Respiratory.

53:07.798 --> 53:10.324
Get me some help down here.
We have to turn him around.

53:10.501 --> 53:12.492
- Turn him, turn him around.
WOMAN 1: Head first.

53:12.669 --> 53:14.660
MAN 1: Nice and easy.
MAN 2: Easy.

53:14.838 --> 53:18.240
WOMAN 1:
Bring him through. Easy, easy.

53:18.642 --> 53:20.542
Bring his head down.
Easy with his head.

53:20.744 --> 53:22.473
All right. Back up, please back up.

53:22.646 --> 53:25.047
- Rawhide's on the table.
- Let's get some oxygen on him.

53:25.249 --> 53:27.343
And get his clothes off, please.

53:27.518 --> 53:29.486
MAN 3:
Lock it down. Clear them out.

53:30.320 --> 53:33.255
WOMAN 2: Get the clothes off.
MAN 3: All right, cut it off.

53:38.862 --> 53:40.227
MAN 4:
Blood pressure reading, stat.

53:40.397 --> 53:42.559
WOMAN 3:
Systolic is 60, he's going into shock.

53:42.766 --> 53:44.131
[SIREN WAILING]

53:44.301 --> 53:48.169
MAN: Headquarters, we're three minutes away.
We're gonna need a secure room.

53:49.873 --> 53:51.864
MAN 1: What do we got?
WOMAN 1: Having trouble breathing.

53:52.042 --> 53:53.874
He collapsed at the door.
He had no pressure.

53:54.044 --> 53:56.536
We got three lines in him,
pressure's coming back up.

53:56.713 --> 54:02.482
We're waiting on a chest x-ray.
I got a gas back, PH is 726, CO2 is 26, O2 is 84.

54:02.653 --> 54:04.917
- It may be a heart attack.
MAN: Is that the--?

54:08.792 --> 54:11.659
Could you take a big breath for me, sir?

54:12.529 --> 54:14.554
Good. I've got good breath signs on the right.

54:14.731 --> 54:16.028
Mmm.

54:16.199 --> 54:17.860
One more big breath.

54:18.035 --> 54:19.935
[GROANING]

54:20.504 --> 54:22.404
I've got no chest sounds on the left.

54:22.573 --> 54:24.098
Turn him on his side.

54:24.308 --> 54:27.608
- Ungh.
- You're doing great, Mr. President.

54:27.811 --> 54:29.370
Oh, my God, he was shot.

54:29.546 --> 54:31.844
There. It's not a heart attack.
That's a shrapnel wound.

54:32.015 --> 54:34.541
And I don't see an exit wound.

54:34.718 --> 54:38.951
Get a test tube, stat. Better get Ben Aaron.
We're gonna need some Xylocaine here.

54:39.122 --> 54:40.385
REAGAN:
I'm sorry to bother you.

54:40.924 --> 54:47.057
-L-- I'm having an awful time breathing.
- You're gonna be all right, Mr. President.

54:47.230 --> 54:48.823
[PANTING]

54:52.536 --> 54:56.973
REAGAN: What do you think?
- I think you're going to be just fine.

54:57.641 --> 55:00.611
Was anyone else hurt?

55:00.777 --> 55:02.438
Two others, but not seriously.

55:02.913 --> 55:05.939
I need you to focus on you.
Can you do that for me?

55:09.353 --> 55:12.152
MAN [ON TV]:
There it <i>is,</i> shots...

55:13.924 --> 55:15.392
BAKER:
Uh-huh.

55:16.860 --> 55:19.852
Yeah. Uh-huh.

55:21.498 --> 55:23.830
Oh, damn it.

55:24.001 --> 55:25.594
What?

55:26.603 --> 55:29.595
We need to tell the public
that the president was not--

55:29.773 --> 55:31.332
Stephen.

55:31.508 --> 55:33.499
Yeah, I understand.

55:34.511 --> 55:36.070
We'll keep this line open.

55:36.246 --> 55:37.805
Yeah, thanks.

55:38.448 --> 55:41.679
It's confirmed. He has been hit.

55:42.919 --> 55:45.183
Doctors are trying to figure out
what to do next.

55:45.389 --> 55:49.087
Ed, you and I should get over there.
David, you stay here. Larry, come with us.

55:52.996 --> 55:56.796
Mrs. Reagan, please, please,
wait for me, please.

55:59.936 --> 56:01.768
Nancy, he's been hit.

56:01.938 --> 56:03.269
They told me he wasn't hit!

56:03.440 --> 56:05.534
At first, they thought it was a heart attack.

56:05.709 --> 56:07.143
I have to see him.

56:07.310 --> 56:09.005
I don't know if that's possible.

56:09.179 --> 56:10.704
I have to see him, Mike.

56:10.914 --> 56:14.680
They don't know how it is with us.
He has to know that I'm here.

56:15.652 --> 56:17.711
I'll make it happen.

56:18.922 --> 56:19.980
Please.

56:20.157 --> 56:24.458
<i>Lyn Nofziger told reporters at the hospital
that the president was not wounded.</i>

56:24.628 --> 56:27.359
<i>He was wounded! Oh, my God!</i>

56:27.531 --> 56:30.865
<i>He was- The president was hit.</i>

56:31.034 --> 56:33.560
<i>He is in stable condition.
All this information...</i>

56:33.737 --> 56:36.729
Mr. Vice President, can you hear me?

56:39.376 --> 56:41.811
This is Secretary Haig.

56:41.978 --> 56:45.243
We-- We've had a serious incident,
and I need--

56:45.449 --> 56:48.885
I'm getting nothing but static on this end.

56:49.052 --> 56:51.680
Dave, get me Baker's secretary.

56:52.022 --> 56:54.013
If you're still headed to Fort Worth...

56:54.191 --> 56:58.822
...I recommend that you return back
to Washington as soon as possible.

56:59.196 --> 57:02.166
Do you read me? Over.

57:02.566 --> 57:04.500
George, this is Al!

57:04.668 --> 57:07.831
Turn around. Turn around.

57:11.842 --> 57:14.504
Can you take and get a message
to Air Force Two by telex?

57:14.678 --> 57:16.510
- Yes. Yes, sir.
- All right.

57:17.013 --> 57:21.280
Dear Mr. Vice President, in the incident
that you would have heard about by now...

57:21.485 --> 57:26.355
- Do we know the caliber of the bullet?
- Yeah, my guys are telling me a .38.

57:26.523 --> 57:28.218
That's too small to be a .38.

57:28.391 --> 57:32.294
No, it's not a .38. It could just be a fragment.
Part of this could be in his belly.

57:32.496 --> 57:35.124
I need to do a peritoneal lavage.
Take him to the operating room.

57:35.298 --> 57:36.629
I need to get this bullet.

57:38.635 --> 57:40.603
- They may have to operate.
- What?

57:40.771 --> 57:43.934
They found a bullet in him, in his left side.
They gotta get it out.

57:44.307 --> 57:46.776
- Jesus.
- We're on a straight line from the hospital.

57:46.943 --> 57:51.710
Gentlemen, anything that is said,
before it is said, we'll discuss at this table.

57:51.882 --> 57:56.877
Any phone calls that anybody gets
with instructions from the hospital...

57:57.053 --> 57:59.044
...will come to this table first.

57:59.222 --> 58:01.452
Right here. Is that clear?

58:06.129 --> 58:09.155
I understand exactly why you're doing that.
I said that, Fred.

58:09.332 --> 58:12.962
Fred, you just sit on them
till I call you back, all right?

58:14.104 --> 58:16.471
Fred Fielding has
the succession papers in order.

58:16.640 --> 58:18.734
- Who told him to do that?
BAKER: He is counsel.

58:18.909 --> 58:22.345
He feels someone needs to be in charge
while the president is in surgery.

58:22.546 --> 58:25.516
I don't know, do they?
Cap has national command authority.

58:25.682 --> 58:29.619
Nobody transferred to Nixon
when Eisenhower went under for his surgery.

58:29.786 --> 58:34.348
If we do this, pass the power of the presidency,
are we gonna panic the country?

58:34.558 --> 58:36.458
Just two months into his presidency.

58:36.626 --> 58:37.923
Definitely very high risk.

58:38.094 --> 58:39.755
Yeah, I say we stand pat.

58:39.930 --> 58:42.126
- And I agree.
- Ag reed.

58:43.567 --> 58:46.662
WOMAN <i>[OVER</i> PA]: <i>All available residents to ER, stat.</i>

58:47.437 --> 58:49.166
[GRUNTING]

58:50.373 --> 58:52.364
Honey. Heh.

58:52.809 --> 58:56.006
L-- I forgot to duck. Heh.

58:58.582 --> 59:01.608
Don't talk. You don't need to talk.

59:03.320 --> 59:08.884
I'm so sorry to interrupt, but there is a lot
of blood coming from his chest tube.

59:09.092 --> 59:11.823
We know the bullet is in your lung,
but we don't know where.

59:11.995 --> 59:13.554
Or what's been injured.

59:13.730 --> 59:17.633
We think we should operate.
We can't take the risk of you bleeding to death.

59:17.801 --> 59:22.739
Whatever you think is best, yeah.

59:22.906 --> 59:24.169
Mommy.

59:24.341 --> 59:26.901
- You're gonna be fine.
- Yeah.

59:33.149 --> 59:34.480
Is he dying?

59:35.986 --> 59:39.081
Ma'am, he will if we don't operate now.

59:39.256 --> 59:41.122
Then do it.

59:48.832 --> 59:51.392
MAN 1: You're doing great, Mr. President.
MAN 2: Give him some room.

59:56.506 --> 59:58.873
- Right this way.
- Who's minding the store?

59:59.042 --> 01:00:01.374
[ALL CHUCKLING]

01:00:01.544 --> 01:00:05.503
WOMAN: Mrs. Reagan, I'm sorry,
you can't go any further.

01:00:05.682 --> 01:00:06.877
MAN 1:
Easy.

01:00:08.251 --> 01:00:11.277
You need to stay with Mrs. Reagan.
Ed, you and I--

01:00:11.454 --> 01:00:12.546
Is that Jim Brady?

01:00:14.925 --> 01:00:17.087
Sweet Jesus.

01:00:18.728 --> 01:00:20.560
- Holy smokes.
- Oh!

01:00:23.166 --> 01:00:26.397
Just keep me posted. If you can't reach me
by phone, send a message.

01:00:26.569 --> 01:00:29.129
- Right here next to me.
- Thank you, general.

01:00:29.306 --> 01:00:31.536
I've just given alerts
to Strategic Air Command.

01:00:31.708 --> 01:00:33.642
- What kind of alert, Cap?
- A stand-by alert.

01:00:33.810 --> 01:00:36.438
- You're not raising readiness?
- Al, don't elevate it.

01:00:37.113 --> 01:00:39.480
I'm not. That's what I just said, Don.

01:00:39.883 --> 01:00:42.545
We have the nuclear codes.
Where'd he put the football?

01:00:42.719 --> 01:00:44.153
It's right here.

01:00:44.321 --> 01:00:46.653
No one makes a move
unless it's cleared by me.

01:00:46.823 --> 01:00:49.053
The helm is right here, in this chair!

01:00:50.327 --> 01:00:53.456
- Constitutionally.
- Al, I'm raising the alert status.

01:00:54.297 --> 01:00:56.129
Do you have any idea what that would do?

01:00:56.566 --> 01:00:58.330
What kind of message that would send?

01:00:58.735 --> 01:01:00.134
We do not panic.

01:01:00.637 --> 01:01:02.901
Goddamn it, Cap!

01:01:05.842 --> 01:01:07.571
Anybody interested in who did it?

01:01:07.744 --> 01:01:09.644
Yes, did he act alone?

01:01:09.813 --> 01:01:13.443
John Warnock Hinckley.
We don't know yet.

01:01:13.616 --> 01:01:15.345
<i>No criminal record.</i>

01:01:15.518 --> 01:01:17.486
<i>He's 25 years old.</i>

01:01:17.654 --> 01:01:19.247
<i>Dropped out of Texas Tech.</i>

01:01:19.990 --> 01:01:23.585
<i>So far, he's refusing to give a statement.</i>

01:01:23.760 --> 01:01:27.253
<i>We're gonna need to find out
what organizations he belongs to.</i>

01:01:28.431 --> 01:01:30.661
Why isn't the Secret Service arresting me?

01:01:31.968 --> 01:01:35.131
The Secret Service doesn't arrest people.
We do.

01:01:44.381 --> 01:01:46.611
He says he wants a lawyer.

01:01:47.884 --> 01:01:49.545
Apparently, he has one in Texas.

01:01:49.753 --> 01:01:50.982
So get him.

01:01:51.154 --> 01:01:52.644
Haven't been able to reach him.

01:01:52.822 --> 01:01:54.654
You want to talk about the shooting?

01:01:54.824 --> 01:01:57.794
I don't know anything about a shooting.

01:01:59.195 --> 01:02:02.460
Maybe the feds will have better luck with him
once they get here.

01:02:02.632 --> 01:02:04.623
They have jurisdiction.

01:02:05.902 --> 01:02:07.870
How do you spell "assassinate"?

01:02:08.038 --> 01:02:12.339
A-S-S-A-S-S-I-N-A-T-E.

01:02:15.478 --> 01:02:16.639
[REAGAN GASPING]

01:02:22.352 --> 01:02:24.548
[WOMAN SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY
OVER PA]

01:02:31.795 --> 01:02:34.196
Jesus, do we need
all the Secret Service in here?

01:02:34.364 --> 01:02:36.230
I'm afraid so, doc.

01:02:36.399 --> 01:02:39.164
Pleur-Evac is still filling with blood.
We're at 2200 cc's.

01:02:39.335 --> 01:02:40.393
Let's get a move on.

01:02:42.305 --> 01:02:45.172
Mr. President, we're gonna take
really good care of you, sir.

01:02:45.341 --> 01:02:47.435
- Good.
- We're gonna be putting you to sleep.

01:02:47.610 --> 01:02:54.038
How are you gonna put me to sleep
if I can hardly breathe now?

01:02:54.217 --> 01:02:56.879
Not to worry. You'll be just fine.

01:02:57.921 --> 01:03:02.358
Well, I hope you're all Republicans.

01:03:02.525 --> 01:03:03.890
[ALL LAUGH]

01:03:04.060 --> 01:03:06.552
Mr. President, today we're all Republicans.

01:03:07.330 --> 01:03:08.820
- Good.
- Okay, let's go.

01:03:14.604 --> 01:03:17.403
MAN <i>[ON RADIO]: Our latest information
is that President Reagan...</i>

01:03:17.574 --> 01:03:20.305
<i>...and Press Secretary Brady
were both taken to-</i>

01:03:20.477 --> 01:03:22.468
[POP MUSIC PLAYING OVER RADIO]

01:03:23.346 --> 01:03:25.110
MAN [snuenue]:
Well, I love a rainy night

01:03:25.281 --> 01:03:26.942
[PHONE RINGING]

01:03:27.584 --> 01:03:30.053
<i>I love to hear the thunder
Watch the lightning</i>

01:03:30.220 --> 01:03:32.712
<i>When it lights up the sky</i>

01:03:33.756 --> 01:03:36.418
<i>You know it makes me feel good</i>

01:03:37.360 --> 01:03:38.657
Hello, Hinckley residence.

01:03:38.862 --> 01:03:40.762
MAN <i>[OVER PHONE]:
Hello, is this Jo Ann Hinckley?</i>

01:03:40.930 --> 01:03:42.659
Yes, who is this?

01:03:42.866 --> 01:03:46.131
<i>This is</i> David O'Hern
from the Washington Post.

01:03:46.302 --> 01:03:48.634
<i>You're John Hinckley': mother?</i>

01:03:48.805 --> 01:03:51.001
Yes. Yes, this is Jo Ann Hinckley.

01:03:51.174 --> 01:03:54.235
<i>Were you aware that President Reagan
was shot this afternoon?</i>

01:03:54.410 --> 01:03:56.003
Well, yes--

01:03:57.147 --> 01:03:59.309
Who are you? What do you want?

01:03:59.482 --> 01:04:04.010
Ma'am, you are aware that your son
was identified as the shooter then?

01:04:04.587 --> 01:04:06.919
What is this, some kind of a sick joke?

01:04:07.090 --> 01:04:08.421
<i>No, this is not.</i>

01:04:08.591 --> 01:04:11.492
Ma'am, has the FBI contacted you yet?

01:04:11.661 --> 01:04:13.129
[GASPING]

01:04:14.764 --> 01:04:16.198
Ma 'am <i>?</i>

01:04:16.900 --> 01:04:18.698
<i>Mrs. Hinckley?</i>

01:04:20.603 --> 01:04:22.970
<i>I'm so sorry, Mrs. Hinckley. Are you there?</i>

01:04:23.139 --> 01:04:24.334
[GROANING]

01:04:24.507 --> 01:04:26.134
<i>Mrs. Hinckley?</i>

01:04:26.309 --> 01:04:27.538
[GUNSHOTS ON TV]

01:04:27.710 --> 01:04:29.041
MAN [ON TV]:
We are receiving word now...

01:04:29.212 --> 01:04:32.614
<i>...that White House Press Secretary
James Brady has passed away.</i>

01:04:33.283 --> 01:04:36.014
<i>He was shot, along with President Reagan,
not long ago...</i>

01:04:36.186 --> 01:04:38.553
<i>was he was exiting the Washington Hilton.</i>

01:04:38.721 --> 01:04:41.713
<i>Officials at the White House
have confirmed this.</i>

01:04:42.125 --> 01:04:45.618
- Is this true, Jim Brady is dead?
- No. He's still on the operating table.

01:04:45.795 --> 01:04:48.730
Make sure that Jim Brady's wife
isn't seeing any of this crap.

01:04:48.932 --> 01:04:51.629
- I will.
- I'm gonna send Speakes to the White House.

01:04:51.801 --> 01:04:55.203
- Somebody's got to set the record straight.
- That's a good idea.

01:04:55.371 --> 01:04:57.738
Who the hell gave out that report?!

01:04:57.941 --> 01:05:00.706
I wanna know every damn thing he says.

01:05:01.244 --> 01:05:03.576
- What's the status on this kid?
- They found some...

01:05:03.746 --> 01:05:07.341
- Just got word Jim Brady is dead.
- They're checking them out.

01:05:07.517 --> 01:05:08.814
What?

01:05:08.985 --> 01:05:11.579
All the networks have picked it up,
Jim Brady is dead.

01:05:11.754 --> 01:05:13.722
Oh, Jesus Christ.

01:05:13.890 --> 01:05:16.860
- We should get a statement ready on that.
- We should.

01:05:17.026 --> 01:05:18.357
[SleHs]

01:05:18.895 --> 01:05:20.829
Bow our heads.

01:05:20.997 --> 01:05:24.092
Say a prayer. Take a moment of silence.

01:05:33.209 --> 01:05:34.677
They're still operating.

01:05:35.345 --> 01:05:38.371
On both Jim and the president.

01:05:39.015 --> 01:05:42.280
Sarah, the coverage is pretty sensational.

01:05:42.485 --> 01:05:44.749
These guys don't know
what they're talking about.

01:05:44.921 --> 01:05:48.186
If I were you,
I would stay away from the TV sets.

01:05:51.494 --> 01:05:53.724
Ron Junior will be here as soon as possible.

01:05:53.896 --> 01:05:58.561
Patti, Michael, Maureen,
they might not be here till tonight.

01:05:59.936 --> 01:06:04.396
I've gotta see about my son.
Um, I left him with my mom's cleaning lady.

01:06:04.774 --> 01:06:06.071
He's fine, Sarah.

01:06:06.242 --> 01:06:08.233
He's fine. He's with your friends now.

01:06:10.146 --> 01:06:11.739
How old is your son?

01:06:12.615 --> 01:06:15.585
Two. His name is Scott.

01:06:19.289 --> 01:06:20.450
Nice in here.

01:06:22.659 --> 01:06:23.990
[SOFTLY]
Yeah.

01:06:24.260 --> 01:06:27.890
- I don't know. But I can confirm. I mean...
- Sir, we need an update.

01:06:28.898 --> 01:06:30.662
[ALL CLAMORING]

01:06:30.833 --> 01:06:33.632
Everybody, hold on.
Everybody, settle down. Settle down.

01:06:33.803 --> 01:06:36.829
James Brady is not dead.
That is erroneous information.

01:06:37.040 --> 01:06:38.804
Is he in critical condition?

01:06:38.975 --> 01:06:40.500
That I do not know.

01:06:40.677 --> 01:06:42.008
About President Reagan.

01:06:42.178 --> 01:06:45.307
Can you give us an understanding
of how serious the chest wound is?

01:06:45.481 --> 01:06:46.573
No, I cannot.

01:06:46.749 --> 01:06:51.084
Larry, we've spoken to the president's brother.
He has received a call from the White House.

01:06:51.254 --> 01:06:53.689
He's been told
that President Reagan is in surgery.

01:06:53.856 --> 01:06:55.824
He's already received blood transfusions.

01:06:55.992 --> 01:06:59.451
Is your information going to continue
to be this far behind other sources?

01:06:59.629 --> 01:07:01.461
No, Cheryl, we'll try to keep up.

01:07:01.864 --> 01:07:06.961
When <i>I</i> first came down here, our <i>initial</i> report
was that the president had not been hit.

01:07:07.136 --> 01:07:11.039
- Who the hell told this guy to go up there?
- Josh, get Larry off the stage.

01:07:11.207 --> 01:07:13.642
- On it, sir.
- He's scaring the crap out of people.

01:07:13.810 --> 01:07:16.643
Larry, who is running
the government right now?

01:07:17.980 --> 01:07:20.779
Uh, I cannot answer that question
at this point.

01:07:20.950 --> 01:07:23.282
What's the status
of the vice president right now?

01:07:23.453 --> 01:07:27.014
Oh, Jesus Christ!
He's turning this into a goddamn disaster.

01:07:28.825 --> 01:07:30.384
Wait.

01:07:33.229 --> 01:07:35.288
- Al, Al?
- Come on.

01:07:35.465 --> 01:07:37.365
Al, wait.

01:07:39.001 --> 01:07:40.628
[ALL CLAMORING]

01:07:46.376 --> 01:07:50.870
I just wanted to let you know that
I'll be down here every 10, 15, or 30 minutes...

01:07:51.047 --> 01:07:53.345
...and let you know exactly what we know.

01:07:53.516 --> 01:07:58.317
And, well, also, when we don't have any
more information, we'll let you know that too.

01:07:58.488 --> 01:07:59.683
That's all I have to say.

01:08:03.159 --> 01:08:04.422
HAIG: Come on.
- Slow down.

01:08:04.627 --> 01:08:07.324
Coming through, make a hole.

01:08:09.365 --> 01:08:11.231
MAN 1: Sir, could you get--?
Get more specifics?

01:08:11.401 --> 01:08:14.200
MAN 2: Mr. Secretary.
MAN 3: Mr. Secretary.

01:08:14.370 --> 01:08:19.171
I'm going to make some statements
in association with today's tragedy.

01:08:19.341 --> 01:08:22.505
WEINBERGER: Raise the alert status.
Only commanders to know.

01:08:22.678 --> 01:08:24.669
- That way, the men can't leak it.
- Guys. It's Al.

01:08:24.846 --> 01:08:26.747
<i>-...we have in the room.
- Hold</i> tight.

01:08:26.916 --> 01:08:32.912
All the officials of the cabinet
who should be here and ready at this time.

01:08:33.089 --> 01:08:39.517
We have informed our friends abroad
of the situation.

01:08:39.694 --> 01:08:44.189
Condition of the president, stable,
now undergoing surgery.

01:08:44.734 --> 01:08:49.103
And there are absolutely no alert measures...

01:08:49.272 --> 01:08:53.072
<i>...that are necessary at this time
or contemplated.</i>

01:08:53.242 --> 01:08:56.303
Now, if you have any questions,
I'll be happy to take them.

01:08:56.479 --> 01:08:58.447
Crisis-- Crisis management.

01:08:58.613 --> 01:09:01.549
Is that's what's going to be put into effect
when Bush arrives?

01:09:01.716 --> 01:09:03.242
Crisis management is in effect.

01:09:03.419 --> 01:09:05.615
Who's making decisions
for the government now?

01:09:06.622 --> 01:09:11.822
Constitutionally, gentlemen,
you have the president, the vice president...

01:09:11.993 --> 01:09:14.053
...and the Secretary of State in that order.

01:09:14.729 --> 01:09:17.756
<i>And should the president decide
to transfer the helm...</i>

01:09:18.401 --> 01:09:20.995
<i>...to the vice president, he-
He will do so.</i>

01:09:21.203 --> 01:09:26.335
As of now, I am in control here
in the White House.

01:09:26.509 --> 01:09:28.603
He doesn't have that authority.

01:09:28.778 --> 01:09:31.145
The Secretary of State is not after Bush.

01:09:31.314 --> 01:09:35.148
No, he's fifth,
after Tip O'Neill and Strom Thurmond.

01:09:35.318 --> 01:09:37.946
He's lost his mind.

01:09:38.120 --> 01:09:40.247
<i>There's surgery now to remove the round.</i>

01:09:40.622 --> 01:09:42.785
Before the surgery,
the president was conscious.

01:09:43.059 --> 01:09:45.084
Right angle. How's he doing, Manny?

01:09:45.261 --> 01:09:48.526
His blood pressure has stabilized, sir.
It's 102 over 54.

01:09:48.731 --> 01:09:52.725
His estimated blood loss is currently 3000 cc's
so far. We're still giving him blood.

01:09:53.135 --> 01:09:57.936
I see the seventh rib is shattered,
and I just can't find the damn bullet.

01:09:58.107 --> 01:09:59.336
This is bad.

01:09:59.809 --> 01:10:03.040
They're strong men, both of them.

01:10:04.747 --> 01:10:06.772
They'll get through this.

01:10:07.283 --> 01:10:09.251
Yes, they will.

01:10:15.491 --> 01:10:16.788
Nothing yet, ma'am.

01:10:19.195 --> 01:10:20.720
[SleHs]

01:10:20.897 --> 01:10:22.524
WOMAN:
Doctor, we have the lateral view.

01:10:22.698 --> 01:10:24.666
Oh, good. Let's take a look.

01:10:31.774 --> 01:10:33.970
Okay, this is an inch from his heart.

01:10:34.143 --> 01:10:36.840
We don't have much time,
let's keep working.

01:10:41.717 --> 01:10:46.382
Al, the chairman is reporting two Soviet
submarines headed for the Atlantic coast.

01:10:47.223 --> 01:10:48.315
How close?

01:10:48.491 --> 01:10:51.552
A nuclear warhead could now reach us
in 10 minutes and 47 seconds.

01:10:51.727 --> 01:10:56.665
- That's two minutes closer than normal.
- Al. Al, are you listening to this?

01:10:56.832 --> 01:11:01.292
I've ordered bomber crews to move from alert
in quarters and on the post in their planes.

01:11:01.671 --> 01:11:04.265
- That should shave off three--
- I said up there!

01:11:04.440 --> 01:11:08.775
Goddamn it, Cap, I'm not a liar.
I said there had been no increased alert.

01:11:08.945 --> 01:11:11.744
I didn't know you were gonna go up there
and say that, Al.

01:11:12.381 --> 01:11:14.372
Let me ask you this, Cap.

01:11:14.550 --> 01:11:17.611
Is the submarines' maneuvering
affecting your decision...

01:11:17.820 --> 01:11:22.280
...or is the fact that the president's out cold
and can't decide for himself?

01:11:22.458 --> 01:11:26.691
No, it's that I have
complete command authority over U.S. forces!

01:11:26.862 --> 01:11:29.422
In this situation,
lam doing what I'm supposed to do!

01:11:29.599 --> 01:11:32.466
You better damn well read the constitution.

01:11:36.105 --> 01:11:38.574
You better read the constitution.

01:11:39.208 --> 01:11:42.200
Doesn't look like a guy
that just shot the president.

01:11:46.349 --> 01:11:49.580
Here's a business card
with a psychiatrisfs phone number.

01:11:50.987 --> 01:11:54.082
- Girlfriend?
- It's from a magazine. Maybe a crush.

01:11:54.256 --> 01:11:55.451
Mm.

01:11:58.127 --> 01:12:00.619
That's a Connecticut phone number.

01:12:01.130 --> 01:12:04.566
He won't talk motive or if he acted alone.

01:12:11.007 --> 01:12:13.669
Seems fascinated with the Secret Service.

01:12:13.876 --> 01:12:16.072
Maybe you should give it a shot.

01:12:18.280 --> 01:12:19.679
Yeah.

01:12:21.417 --> 01:12:23.078
Sponge stick.

01:12:25.988 --> 01:12:28.923
- How long has he been under, Manny?
MANNY: It's been 85 minutes, sir.

01:12:29.091 --> 01:12:31.992
Jesus. Sponge stick again.

01:12:32.161 --> 01:12:34.653
Excuse me.
Uh, what are you thinking, doc?

01:12:34.830 --> 01:12:38.027
I think you're gonna need
to step out of the field. Back up.

01:12:40.469 --> 01:12:41.959
In my brows.

01:12:42.138 --> 01:12:46.598
<i>We have just heard
from Secretary of State Alexander Haig...</i>

01:12:46.776 --> 01:12:48.835
<i>...who has given us~</i>

01:12:49.278 --> 01:12:51.838
<i>Who has given us an update
on the situation.</i>

01:12:52.014 --> 01:12:55.780
<i>We are told
that the president is in surgery now...</i>

01:12:56.318 --> 01:12:58.878
<i>...that he was wounded in the lung.
We know~</i>

01:12:59.055 --> 01:13:01.046
We knew, of course, earlier that he was hit.

01:13:10.800 --> 01:13:12.199
[EXHALES]

01:13:13.569 --> 01:13:14.661
<i>AARON:
Right angle.</i>

01:13:14.837 --> 01:13:16.202
[MONITOR BEEPING]

01:13:16.372 --> 01:13:17.430
Pick up.

01:13:18.007 --> 01:13:19.475
Come on, pick up.

01:13:19.642 --> 01:13:20.666
Give me ex stat.

01:13:24.880 --> 01:13:26.644
Where is this damn thing?

01:13:26.816 --> 01:13:29.649
Hundred and four minutes, Ben.
Coming to the edge here.

01:13:30.753 --> 01:13:33.415
Maybe we should just close him up.

01:13:33.589 --> 01:13:35.489
He's lost over 50 percent of his blood.

01:13:35.658 --> 01:13:39.253
And I can't stop the bleeding
while I'm searching for the bullet.

01:13:40.329 --> 01:13:42.696
Maybe we should just leave it in.

01:13:46.769 --> 01:13:48.168
Having a good time there, Ben?

01:13:49.205 --> 01:13:50.263
Yeah, wonderful.

01:13:50.473 --> 01:13:51.838
Just wonderful.

01:13:56.011 --> 01:13:57.638
Right angle.

01:14:01.984 --> 01:14:03.543
Hey, John.

01:14:04.120 --> 01:14:07.249
Stephen Colo, Secret Service.

01:14:08.224 --> 01:14:09.885
How you doing?

01:14:10.392 --> 01:14:12.952
- My wrists hurt.
- Hm.

01:14:13.129 --> 01:14:15.427
We'll get that taken care of for you.

01:14:17.199 --> 01:14:19.793
- You know why you're here, John?
- Mm-hm.

01:14:20.002 --> 01:14:25.441
You're in violation of U.S. Code 1751,
the attempted assassination of the president.

01:14:28.878 --> 01:14:30.869
We just need to know,
was anyone else involved?

01:14:31.814 --> 01:14:34.579
No, it was just me.

01:14:36.886 --> 01:14:38.820
So can you tell me why you did it, then?

01:14:42.825 --> 01:14:45.385
Come on, John,
we already know things about you...

01:14:45.561 --> 01:14:47.290
...because we've been checking.

01:14:48.764 --> 01:14:50.732
I've been seeing a psychiatrist lately.

01:14:50.900 --> 01:14:52.129
I can tell you that.

01:14:52.301 --> 01:14:54.429
Well, what's that all about?

01:14:55.070 --> 01:14:57.095
I have no direction in life.

01:15:01.343 --> 01:15:03.277
I'd like to talk to my lawyer.

01:15:05.781 --> 01:15:10.776
You know, John, any stuff you can tell me now
will help you on down the line.

01:15:12.588 --> 01:15:14.181
Yeah.

01:15:15.491 --> 01:15:18.483
I just-- I think I need to talk to my lawyer.

01:15:24.300 --> 01:15:27.133
- Okay.
- Is this on television?

01:15:27.303 --> 01:15:29.465
No, it's-- It's not being taped.

01:15:29.638 --> 01:15:31.470
It's not what I meant.

01:15:31.941 --> 01:15:33.431
Is this on television?

01:15:38.013 --> 01:15:41.381
Yeah. National television.

01:15:42.718 --> 01:15:44.379
Will it--?

01:15:44.587 --> 01:15:46.612
Will it affect other people?

01:15:46.789 --> 01:15:49.121
Will they be pulled into it?

01:15:49.291 --> 01:15:50.520
Will she--?

01:15:50.693 --> 01:15:52.161
Will they see it?

01:15:52.828 --> 01:15:55.126
You mean, like your friends
and your parents?

01:15:55.297 --> 01:15:56.594
And others.

01:15:58.234 --> 01:16:00.669
We know about the phone number
in your wallet, John.

01:16:00.836 --> 01:16:02.998
The one from Connecticut?

01:16:04.707 --> 01:16:07.677
Well, if you know that,
then you know everything.

01:16:13.482 --> 01:16:15.416
[MONITOR BEEPING]

01:16:29.865 --> 01:16:31.856
[SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY]

01:16:36.572 --> 01:16:38.062
Wait.

01:16:41.043 --> 01:16:42.636
Bucket.

01:16:51.453 --> 01:16:52.784
I'll take that.

01:16:52.955 --> 01:16:55.788
We're not done.
Let's keep on going. Sponge stick.

01:16:55.958 --> 01:16:59.292
<i>Well, Lyn Nofziger said
he would be coming out of surgery shortly...</i>

01:16:59.461 --> 01:17:01.657
<i>...that his condition is good and stable...</i>

01:17:02.564 --> 01:17:05.625
- Yes!
- Hey, Mike, yeah, we just heard.

01:17:05.801 --> 01:17:07.462
It's fantastic news.

01:17:07.670 --> 01:17:12.267
<i>...and is probably, I suppose,
a 70-year-old man is able to withstand...</i>

01:17:12.441 --> 01:17:16.571
<i>...what must be the natural shock
of the surgery, certainly of being shot.</i>

01:17:16.745 --> 01:17:18.270
[SIGHING]
Sarah.

01:17:21.250 --> 01:17:22.445
I'm so happy for You-

01:17:22.618 --> 01:17:24.484
Thank you.

01:17:24.687 --> 01:17:29.181
I'm going home now. The doctors say
he's gonna be sedated all night, so...

01:17:33.595 --> 01:17:34.926
[SOFTLY]
I'm so scared.

01:17:35.097 --> 01:17:37.657
MAN: <i>...that</i> a <i>large-caliber bullet
will do more damage...</i>

01:17:37.833 --> 01:17:39.130
<i>...in both the president's case...</i>

01:17:39.301 --> 01:17:42.601
They're strong men, remember?

01:17:42.771 --> 01:17:47.072
<i>Dr. Demayo was emphasizing the potential
danger of the small-caliber bullet...</i>

01:17:47.242 --> 01:17:52.908
<i>...uh, which can apparently do so much damage
as it's moving around inside the body.</i>

01:17:55.217 --> 01:17:59.154
<i>No, it doesn't explode.
I mean, that's the dum-dum kind.</i>

01:18:00.222 --> 01:18:01.621
[DOOR CLOSES]

01:18:02.591 --> 01:18:04.923
Thanks. Colonel Jones.

01:18:07.529 --> 01:18:09.327
[SPEAKS INDISTINCTLY]

01:18:10.733 --> 01:18:12.861
The Soviet subs are turning around.

01:18:13.035 --> 01:18:14.127
There's no threat.

01:18:14.303 --> 01:18:15.600
There never was.

01:18:15.771 --> 01:18:18.968
The Soviets were merely changing battalions.

01:18:19.675 --> 01:18:21.370
I just spoke with Baker.

01:18:21.543 --> 01:18:24.638
The vice president should be here by 1900.

01:18:24.813 --> 01:18:27.680
WEINBERGER:
Guess you can stand down now, Al.

01:18:29.985 --> 01:18:31.976
[MONITOR BEEPING]

01:18:36.558 --> 01:18:39.186
[WOMAN SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY
OVER PA]

01:19:09.191 --> 01:19:11.182
[WAILING]

01:19:26.341 --> 01:19:27.604
[MONITOR BEEPING]

01:19:40.055 --> 01:19:42.683
[WOMAN SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY
OVER PA]

01:19:44.259 --> 01:19:45.727
Oh, please, please. Mister--

01:19:45.894 --> 01:19:49.421
Mr. Reagan, Mr. Reagan,
that tube is in there to help you breathe.

01:19:49.598 --> 01:19:52.397
I don't want to have to tie
your hands down. Sir?

01:19:52.568 --> 01:19:54.127
Okay?

01:19:56.338 --> 01:19:57.931
All right.

01:19:59.708 --> 01:20:01.938
You want to write something down?

01:20:04.246 --> 01:20:05.975
Here you go.

01:20:07.850 --> 01:20:09.443
Here you go.

01:20:24.600 --> 01:20:27.900
So, apparently,
the bullet ricocheted off the limo.

01:20:28.070 --> 01:20:30.630
That's why it was flat and so hard to find.

01:20:32.774 --> 01:20:35.971
- The all-important dairy bill.
REAGAN: Oh...

01:20:37.012 --> 01:20:40.812
Oh, I should have known that you fellas
wouldn't let me miss a staff meeting.

01:20:40.983 --> 01:20:43.350
[ALL LAUGH]

01:20:43.519 --> 01:20:46.784
Well, it is essential the world see
we're still open for business.

01:20:46.955 --> 01:20:49.481
- And that you sign.
- And not Al Haig.

01:20:49.658 --> 01:20:50.750
N ow, n ow.

01:20:52.127 --> 01:20:54.459
- Long story.
- We'll tell you about it later.

01:20:54.630 --> 01:20:56.689
For now, just focus on getting better.

01:20:56.899 --> 01:20:58.833
- After you sign the bill.
- Okay.

01:20:59.968 --> 01:21:01.493
[REAGAN SIGHS]

01:21:02.704 --> 01:21:05.639
DEAVER: That should put
the fear of God into the Soviets.

01:21:10.979 --> 01:21:12.447
[EXHALES]

01:21:12.614 --> 01:21:16.482
This, uh, kid who--

01:21:16.652 --> 01:21:18.780
Who shot me...

01:21:19.188 --> 01:21:22.818
...what was the guy--?
What was the guy's beef?

01:21:26.361 --> 01:21:28.193
We don't know.

01:21:28.931 --> 01:21:32.492
Seems he was just some crazy,
mixed-up kid.

01:21:33.835 --> 01:21:38.705
L-- I was hoping it was the KGB. But on second
thought, then he wouldn't have missed.

01:21:38.874 --> 01:21:41.309
[ALL CHUCKLE]

01:21:41.476 --> 01:21:42.637
[EXHALES]

01:21:42.811 --> 01:21:44.643
What was the young man's name?

01:21:45.380 --> 01:21:46.973
John Hinckley.

01:21:49.051 --> 01:21:50.746
Hinckley.

01:21:51.386 --> 01:21:52.717
[EXHALES]

01:21:53.822 --> 01:21:55.586
I will pray for him.

01:22:06.535 --> 01:22:08.230
JO ANN:
John.

01:22:10.973 --> 01:22:12.839
[SOBBING]
I love you.

01:22:13.008 --> 01:22:15.943
Nothing is ever gonna change that.

01:22:16.111 --> 01:22:17.601
I know.

01:22:17.779 --> 01:22:21.545
We want you to know we're getting you
the best lawyers we can afford.

01:22:21.717 --> 01:22:25.517
- Good, thank you.
- The psychiatric doctors here, they're gonna--

01:22:25.687 --> 01:22:28.247
They're gonna give you all the help
that they can.

01:22:28.423 --> 01:22:31.586
First step, as we've been told,
is a grand jury appearance.

01:22:31.760 --> 01:22:33.023
Do you understand?

01:22:33.195 --> 01:22:34.390
Yeah.

01:22:34.563 --> 01:22:36.554
Will Jodie be there?

01:22:38.433 --> 01:22:40.595
- Um...
- Will she?

01:22:43.872 --> 01:22:45.897
He really is in remarkable health.

01:22:46.074 --> 01:22:47.371
It's very important to him.

01:22:47.542 --> 01:22:51.410
I mean, I don't know if we would've had
the same results if he wasn't.

01:22:52.748 --> 01:22:55.149
I did want to warn you though,
things may be different now.

01:22:56.118 --> 01:22:58.746
- What do you mean?
- Well, he lost a lot of blood.

01:22:58.920 --> 01:23:01.821
And we used universal type O negative.

01:23:02.324 --> 01:23:03.917
- You know, that's the type--
- Yes.

01:23:04.092 --> 01:23:07.585
I'd have much rather used his type,
but we weren't sure at the time...

01:23:07.763 --> 01:23:10.630
...and he was about to go into shock.

01:23:10.799 --> 01:23:13.291
Also, the transfusions were cold.

01:23:13.468 --> 01:23:20.340
So that combined with the anesthesia
and the president's age, seeing that he is 70--

01:23:20.542 --> 01:23:22.135
What are you trying to say, doctor?

01:23:24.246 --> 01:23:25.611
It may be a long recovery.

01:23:26.581 --> 01:23:31.280
And in some ways,
the president may not come all the way back.

01:23:32.254 --> 01:23:35.485
This was a traumatic event, Mrs. Reagan.

01:23:37.125 --> 01:23:41.062
Your husband will likely have
a very slow recovery.

01:23:44.933 --> 01:23:46.560
[MONITOR BEEPING]

01:23:51.673 --> 01:23:54.301
[WOMAN SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY
OVER PA]

01:24:12.327 --> 01:24:15.353
Jim. Hi.

01:24:17.999 --> 01:24:19.660
Sarah.

01:24:22.971 --> 01:24:24.564
We're thinking of you.

01:24:24.740 --> 01:24:26.970
Mr. President, we're ready for you.

01:24:29.044 --> 01:24:31.911
Uh... I walked into this hospital.

01:24:33.014 --> 01:24:34.846
I would like to walk back out.

01:24:37.919 --> 01:24:39.011
Thank you.

01:24:44.192 --> 01:24:46.388
[ALL CHEERING]

01:24:46.561 --> 01:24:49.258
Congratulations, Mr. President.

01:24:53.935 --> 01:24:55.232
Bye, sir.

01:24:55.404 --> 01:24:57.498
Congrats, Mr. President.

01:24:59.374 --> 01:25:01.240
MAN 1:
Mr. President!

01:25:02.210 --> 01:25:04.076
Mr. President, how are you feeling?

01:25:04.246 --> 01:25:05.441
Great.

01:25:05.647 --> 01:25:06.910
What are you gonna do
when you get home?

01:25:07.082 --> 01:25:08.106
Huh?

01:25:08.283 --> 01:25:10.047
What are you gonna do
when you get home?

01:25:10.218 --> 01:25:11.686
Sit down!

01:25:11.853 --> 01:25:13.685
[CROWD LAUGHS]

01:25:21.196 --> 01:25:23.597
<i>Don't you see
what a wonderful thing this can be?</i>

01:25:23.765 --> 01:25:24.857
<i>But we need you, John.</i>

01:25:25.033 --> 01:25:27.695
MAN: You're hooked,
<i>I</i> can see that right now. They got you.

01:25:27.869 --> 01:25:29.963
<i>Well, I'm through.</i>

01:25:31.740 --> 01:25:34.710
<i>I been trying to get you up
to the Columbia River country.</i>

01:25:34.876 --> 01:25:38.608
<i>It was your glass arm, then it was the radio,
and now it's the John Doe clubs.</i>

01:25:38.780 --> 01:25:40.475
<i>Well, I ain't waiting another minute.</i>

01:25:44.052 --> 01:25:46.680
Ronnie, I need to talk to you
about something.

01:25:47.322 --> 01:25:48.983
Okay.

01:25:49.191 --> 01:25:50.420
Um...

01:25:50.592 --> 01:25:53.391
I was talking to Merv Griffin on the phone.

01:25:53.562 --> 01:25:55.553
Oh, and how is Merv?

01:25:55.730 --> 01:25:58.722
[CHUCKLING]
He's fine. He says hi.

01:25:58.900 --> 01:26:03.633
And, uh, he thinks he has someone
who might be able to help us.

01:26:03.805 --> 01:26:05.102
He--

01:26:06.074 --> 01:26:09.567
Do you remember
when he introduced me to that astrologer?

01:26:10.212 --> 01:26:12.146
- No. Heh.
- Well, he did.

01:26:12.948 --> 01:26:16.316
Her name is Joan Quigley,
and she is very good.

01:26:16.485 --> 01:26:19.182
I mean, she is really very good.

01:26:19.354 --> 01:26:21.345
She has a knack, and...

01:26:22.724 --> 01:26:24.317
Okay.

01:26:24.493 --> 01:26:30.159
He told me that she predicted that March 30th
wasn't going to be a good day for you.

01:26:30.332 --> 01:26:31.857
Are you-r;

01:26:32.033 --> 01:26:37.767
Are you telling me this woman knew
I was going to be shot on March 30th?

01:26:37.939 --> 01:26:41.842
No. No, no, no.
That's not what I'm saying at all.

01:26:42.010 --> 01:26:44.445
What I'm saying is,
she could have warned us.

01:26:45.614 --> 01:26:51.178
If we had been in touch with her, we might
have been on the lookout for something and--

01:26:51.353 --> 01:26:54.653
Maybe you would never have gone
and given that speech.

01:26:54.823 --> 01:26:57.121
Oh, so you--

01:26:57.292 --> 01:26:59.124
You wanna get advice from this woman.

01:26:59.294 --> 01:27:02.787
Yes. In fact, I already have been.

01:27:02.964 --> 01:27:04.898
Mommy, you and I...

01:27:05.066 --> 01:27:07.228
-...we might think this is a good idea.
- Yes.

01:27:07.402 --> 01:27:09.063
And maybe even Michael.

01:27:09.271 --> 01:27:12.297
But everyone else--
I mean, if they found out--

01:27:12.474 --> 01:27:16.377
- Nobody would find out.
- But you can't keep secrets around here.

01:27:16.545 --> 01:27:18.980
- You know--
- We would-- We would keep it secret.

01:27:19.147 --> 01:27:20.740
We would.

01:27:20.916 --> 01:27:23.851
- You-- You have been far too open, Ronnie.
- What?

01:27:24.019 --> 01:27:28.650
You-- You-- You have to protect yourself,
and if you're not going to protect yourself...

01:27:28.823 --> 01:27:31.087
-...I will.
- I have people to protect me.

01:27:31.293 --> 01:27:33.318
Oh, yes, and look how that turned out.

01:27:33.495 --> 01:27:36.362
- But the press--
- I don't care about the press.

01:27:37.232 --> 01:27:41.794
I don't care about your staff or anybody else.
I care about you.

01:27:42.837 --> 01:27:45.807
And this is not going to happen again,
do you hear me?

01:27:47.008 --> 01:27:50.569
L-- I could not go through this
one more time.

01:27:51.613 --> 01:27:53.081
L-- I would just die.

01:27:53.248 --> 01:27:55.114
Well-- Well, you and me both.

01:27:55.317 --> 01:27:58.082
Oh, that's not funny!
I'm sorry. I'm sorry, I'm sorry.

01:27:58.253 --> 01:27:59.687
[LAUGHING]

01:27:59.854 --> 01:28:01.083
[sum-nus]

01:28:03.224 --> 01:28:05.056
Please.

01:28:05.961 --> 01:28:08.953
Will you let me hire an astrologer?

01:28:09.564 --> 01:28:14.764
I know it sounds crazy,
but I-- I just-- I have to.

01:28:14.936 --> 01:28:18.463
Well, all right.

01:28:21.910 --> 01:28:27.440
You know, Mommy,
I have been thinking too.

01:28:28.750 --> 01:28:34.553
I think maybe I was spared for a reason.

01:28:35.757 --> 01:28:37.657
What do you mean?

01:28:37.859 --> 01:28:43.059
Maybe it wasn't an accident.

01:28:43.765 --> 01:28:50.068
Maybe the rest of my days here on earth...

01:28:50.872 --> 01:28:53.933
...they belong to Him.

01:28:56.811 --> 01:28:59.007
With a capital H.

01:29:10.625 --> 01:29:12.252
[GROANING]

01:29:28.143 --> 01:29:32.273
My dear...

01:29:33.648 --> 01:29:35.639
...Mr...

01:29:36.851 --> 01:29:38.910
...President.

01:29:43.692 --> 01:29:45.990
HAIG: I should compose something
with a firmer tone...

01:29:46.161 --> 01:29:47.356
...and from the State Department.

01:29:47.529 --> 01:29:51.488
- The Russian president is testing us.
- Well, I want it to be personal, Al.

01:29:52.567 --> 01:29:55.537
- Why?
- Because it is personal.

01:29:57.138 --> 01:30:00.870
Mr. President, this is the worst possible thing
you could do right now.

01:30:01.342 --> 01:30:05.245
A grain embargo, that's our only
bargaining chip, and you're just giving it away.

01:30:05.447 --> 01:30:07.814
Well, I don't see it that way.

01:30:07.982 --> 01:30:11.543
You know the Russians will view this as weak.
Worse than Carter.

01:30:11.720 --> 01:30:15.486
And make no mistake,
they will take advantage.

01:30:15.657 --> 01:30:19.218
- We'll just have to take that chance, won't we?
- What about your supporters?

01:30:19.394 --> 01:30:22.227
- They didn't elect you to capitulate.
- That is enough, Al.

01:30:22.397 --> 01:30:24.559
- It's your conservative base.
- I said, shut up!

01:30:26.668 --> 01:30:32.198
And why in the hell can't I open the doors
to bargain with Brezhnev?

01:30:32.874 --> 01:30:36.105
When I was in Sacramento,
I had a lot of people giving me advice...

01:30:36.277 --> 01:30:40.339
...and they wanted it all or nothing,
and they wanted it all at once!

01:30:40.515 --> 01:30:44.213
And I learned a long time ago
negotiating union contracts...

01:30:44.385 --> 01:30:48.253
...that you seldom get everything you want.

01:30:48.423 --> 01:30:53.691
That's what I told these radical Republicans,
and that's what I'm telling you now, Al.

01:30:53.862 --> 01:30:57.298
Why would I risk losing everything
if I can get 75 percent of what I want?

01:31:00.135 --> 01:31:05.039
The last time I checked, I am in control here.

01:31:07.909 --> 01:31:12.073
Now, please, send the letter, Al.

01:31:12.247 --> 01:31:14.477
- Understood.
- As is.

01:31:14.649 --> 01:31:16.413
Understood, sir.

01:31:24.592 --> 01:31:25.923
[sum-nus]

01:31:29.831 --> 01:31:32.892
NANCY: I was told the trip had been canceled.
- The president insisted.

01:31:33.067 --> 01:31:35.434
After Jim and Ed cowed him into it.

01:31:35.603 --> 01:31:37.799
Michael, he was not to travel yesterday.

01:31:37.972 --> 01:31:41.465
I apologize.
You have my word it won't happen again.

01:31:41.643 --> 01:31:43.634
- It mustn't.
- I get it, I understand.

01:31:43.812 --> 01:31:48.045
You don't get it. You don't understand.
It is your job to protect him!

01:31:49.317 --> 01:31:50.842
He's...

01:31:52.854 --> 01:31:54.413
He's changed.

01:31:55.924 --> 01:31:57.756
Don't you see it?

01:31:58.126 --> 01:31:59.491
Honestly, Nancy, no.

01:32:00.128 --> 01:32:01.596
He has.

01:32:02.764 --> 01:32:05.699
- The doctor said we're looking--
- I don't wanna hear it.

01:32:06.201 --> 01:32:08.693
I don't need your advice,
I don't need your comfort.

01:32:08.870 --> 01:32:11.305
- I need you to listen to me.
- Understood.

01:32:13.274 --> 01:32:14.435
Thank you.

01:32:19.614 --> 01:32:21.981
- You'll handle the bells and whistles.
- Of course.

01:32:22.150 --> 01:32:24.517
It's very important
that we take advantage of this time.

01:32:24.686 --> 01:32:27.781
Mr. President,
your poll numbers are through the roof.

01:32:27.956 --> 01:32:29.981
Well, they should be, I got shot.

01:32:30.158 --> 01:32:31.284
[ALL LAUGH]

01:32:31.459 --> 01:32:33.393
You're like a hero in one of your movies.

01:32:33.595 --> 01:32:35.029
Unbelievable.

01:32:35.196 --> 01:32:37.961
The economic recovery bill
is ready to go up for a vote...

01:32:38.132 --> 01:32:40.123
...but this good will, it won't last long.

01:32:40.301 --> 01:32:42.668
So we need to do this speech
before congress soon.

01:32:42.837 --> 01:32:45.363
O'Neill says
he thinks we're taking advantage.

01:32:45.540 --> 01:32:47.531
Let him see what happens
if he even tries to stop us.

01:32:47.709 --> 01:32:49.541
No, he won't. He already said he won't.

01:32:49.711 --> 01:32:53.011
- Agent McCarthy and officer...?
- Delahanty.

01:32:53.181 --> 01:32:56.811
Only survivor who won't be
able to attend is Jim.

01:32:56.985 --> 01:32:58.419
Ah...

01:32:59.220 --> 01:33:00.847
What's the latest?

01:33:01.022 --> 01:33:05.323
DEAVER: Doctors say he'll pull through,
but they doubt he'll walk again.

01:33:06.027 --> 01:33:10.260
And there is some talk, Mr. President,
he suffered some brain damage.

01:33:10.899 --> 01:33:12.628
Damn.

01:33:15.069 --> 01:33:19.199
What do you say, as a tribute to Jim...

01:33:19.374 --> 01:33:23.868
...we let him keep the title
of press secretary no matter what?

01:33:24.045 --> 01:33:25.535
- That's a great idea.
- Of course.

01:33:27.015 --> 01:33:30.110
- Well, shall we talk dates for the speech?
- Ah.

01:33:30.285 --> 01:33:33.380
Could we wrap this up?
Doctors only give me a couple hours a day.

01:33:33.554 --> 01:33:34.851
Of course.

01:33:35.023 --> 01:33:38.891
All right, we've got the 27th or the 28th.
That's a Monday or a Tuesday.

01:33:39.060 --> 01:33:41.256
Uh, Monday's no good.

01:33:41.429 --> 01:33:43.363
What's wrong with it?

01:33:43.531 --> 01:33:45.795
The first lady feels it's bad for the president.

01:33:48.369 --> 01:33:52.704
Is there, uh, something going on
I don't know about?

01:33:53.374 --> 01:33:54.398
Mr. President?

01:33:54.876 --> 01:33:58.244
Oh, Jim, let's just do Tuesday. Heh.

01:33:58.413 --> 01:34:00.882
Monday, everyone's asleep anyway,
I know I am.

01:34:01.049 --> 01:34:02.244
[CHUCKLING]

01:34:03.418 --> 01:34:06.786
<i>The president and his aides
do not concede their plan is a gamble...</i>

01:34:06.955 --> 01:34:09.754
<i>...but Mr. Reagan doesn't intend
to argue the point tonight.</i>

01:34:09.924 --> 01:34:12.723
<i>He is going to Capitol Hill
not to debate his program...</i>

01:34:12.894 --> 01:34:16.762
<i>...but to build a new and, he hopes,
irresistible wave of emotion behind it...</i>

01:34:17.131 --> 01:34:18.792
[GROANING]

01:34:20.735 --> 01:34:22.829
<i>...in the wake of the assassination attempt.</i>

01:34:23.004 --> 01:34:25.632
Here, let me.

01:34:26.240 --> 01:34:27.605
Thank you, Mommy.

01:34:27.775 --> 01:34:32.076
<i>All in all, the president hopes congress
will feel they must vote for his program...</i>

01:34:32.246 --> 01:34:35.944
<i>...both because it is right
and because it is his.</i>

01:34:36.117 --> 01:34:39.519
<i>Sam Donaldson, ABC News,
the White House.</i>

01:34:43.224 --> 01:34:44.623
[REAGAN CHUCKLES]

01:34:59.140 --> 01:35:00.505
[EXHALES]

01:35:08.850 --> 01:35:10.545
All set?

01:35:11.519 --> 01:35:13.351
I am now.

01:35:18.326 --> 01:35:23.992
Mr. Speaker,
the president of the United States!

01:35:24.165 --> 01:35:26.156
[ALL CHEERING]

01:35:28.269 --> 01:35:29.464
Congratulations.

01:35:29.637 --> 01:35:31.503
Good to see you.

01:35:32.907 --> 01:35:35.638
- How are you? Good to see you, sir.
- John. Hey, John.

01:35:36.277 --> 01:35:39.008
- How is Allison?
- Wonderful.

01:35:41.215 --> 01:35:42.683
How are you? Thank you.

01:35:42.850 --> 01:35:43.908
It's good to be back.

01:35:44.085 --> 01:35:45.553
Hi.

01:36:41.609 --> 01:36:43.134
[GUNSHOTS]

01:36:54.155 --> 01:36:55.850
I love you, John.

01:37:05.600 --> 01:37:07.591
[CHEERING CONTINUES]

01:37:18.479 --> 01:37:20.811
<i>Thank you very much.</i>

01:37:31.125 --> 01:37:34.652
<i>You wouldn't wanna talk me
into an encore, would you?</i>

01:37:34.829 --> 01:37:36.263
[ALL LAUGH]

01:37:43.905 --> 01:37:48.308
<i>REAGAN". My fellow Americans,
I have recently been told...</i>

01:37:48.476 --> 01:37:55.041
<i>...that I am one of the millions of Americans
who will</i> be <i>afflicted with Alzheimer's disease.</i>

01:37:55.216 --> 01:37:58.447
At the moment, <i>I</i> feel just fine.

01:37:59.053 --> 01:38:03.422
<i>I intend to live the remainder of the years
God gives me on this earth...</i>

01:38:03.958 --> 01:38:07.053
<i>"doing the things I have always done.</i>

01:38:07.228 --> 01:38:13.725
<i>I will continue to share life's journey
with my beloved Nancy and my family.</i>

01:38:14.702 --> 01:38:20.072
<i>I</i> plan to enjoy the great outdoors and stay
<i>in</i> touch with my friends and supporters.

01:38:21.509 --> 01:38:25.309
<i>Unfortunately,
as Alzheimer's disease progresses...</i>

01:38:25.479 --> 01:38:27.971
<i>...the family often bears a heavy burden.</i>

01:38:29.951 --> 01:38:33.319
<i>I only wish there was some way
I could spare Nancy...</i>

01:38:33.487 --> 01:38:36.252
<i>"from this painful experience.</i>

01:38:38.593 --> 01:38:42.928
<i>In closing, let me thank you,
the American people...</i>

01:38:43.097 --> 01:38:48.661
<i>...for giving me the great honor
of allowing me to serve as your president.</i>

01:38:48.836 --> 01:38:52.534
<i>When the Lord calls me home,
whenever that may he...</i>

01:38:52.707 --> 01:38:56.109
<i>...I will leave the greatest love
for this country of ours...</i>

01:38:56.277 --> 01:39:00.180
<i>...and eternal optimism for its future.</i>

01:39:01.349 --> 01:39:07.379
<i>I now begin the journey
that will lead me into the sunset of my life.</i>

01:39:07.555 --> 01:39:14.359
<i>I know that for America,
there will always be a bright dawn ahead.</i>

01:39:39.820 --> 01:39:42.551
You and I have a rendezvous with destiny.

01:39:42.723 --> 01:39:46.819
We'll preserve for our children this,
the last best hope of man on earth...

01:39:47.028 --> 01:39:50.726
...or sentence them to take the last step
into a thousand years of darkness.

01:39:50.898 --> 01:39:54.095
I will not make age an issue
of this campaign.

01:39:54.268 --> 01:40:00.935
I am not going to exploit for political purposes
my opponent's youth and inexperience.

01:40:01.108 --> 01:40:03.475
[ALL LAUGHING]

01:40:03.644 --> 01:40:08.343
We can win all together,
but let us at least be sure of one thing...

01:40:08.549 --> 01:40:11.280
...if it should be our destiny to fail...

01:40:11.452 --> 01:40:15.320
...let's not fail because we weren't together,
because we didn't stick together.

01:40:15.489 --> 01:40:17.617
[CROWD CHEERING]

01:40:17.792 --> 01:40:21.126
I will faithfully execute the office
of President of the United States.

01:40:21.295 --> 01:40:26.131
A few months ago, I told the American people
I did not trade arms for hostages.

01:40:26.300 --> 01:40:29.793
My heart and my best intentions
still tell me that's true...

01:40:29.970 --> 01:40:33.600
...but the facts and the evidence
tell me it is not.

01:40:33.774 --> 01:40:38.541
As the Tower board reported,
what began as a strategic opening to Iran...

01:40:38.713 --> 01:40:43.674
...deteriorated in its implementation
into trading arms for hostages.

01:40:43.851 --> 01:40:48.015
Mr. Gorbachev, tear down this wall.

01:40:48.189 --> 01:40:50.180
[CROWD CHEERING]
